title: i_got_a_glock_in_my_'rari_(meme)
body:
A meme referencing the famous photo of [[LeBron James]] [[slam_dunk_(basketball)|dunking]] a [[basketball_(object)|]] after receiving it from [[Dwyane Wade]], who has his [[spread_arms|arms out]] in the photo, during the [[2010]] Miami Heat vs. Milwaukee Bucks [[basketball]] game. The name is derived from a lyric in the song [b]679[/b] by [[Fetty Wap]], which is occasionally associated with the image in videos.

h4. Examples

* !asset #23704115: Origin

h4. External links

* "YouTube: Dwayne Wade to LeBron James":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H_TapNgp_rQ

title: undressing
body:
When someone is in the middle of taking off their clothes. When you are unsure whether clothes are being taken off or put on, use this tag. If they are clearly being put on, use [[dressing]] instead.

Not to be confused with [[wardrobe malfunction]], which is when clothing comes off accidentally, or [[unworn clothes]], which is when the character is already [[completely nude|fully undressed]].

Please see “Removing *” tags for removing specific items of clothing.

h4. See also

* [[undressing another]] - when someone is taking off someone else's clothing.
* [[dressing]]
* [[assisted exposure]]
* topic #1075

title: enkidu_(fate)
body:
[[Fate (series)|]] character first appearing in flashbacks in [[Fate/Zero]] and [[Fate/Extra CCC]]. They are the "False" Lancer-class servant of [[Wolf (fate)|]] in [[Fate/strange fake]], and first appear in [[Fate/Grand Order]] during the [[Babylonia (fate/grand order)|]] singularity. They are [[Gilgamesh (fate)|]]'s closest friend and the namesake for [[enkidu (weapon) (fate)|his chains]], which Enkidu also utilizes in combat.

They are depicted as a long, [[green hair]]ed [[androgynous]] homunculus with [[green eyes]] and wearing a [[robe]]. Their "[[trap|appearance of a woman]]" is due to taking on the appearance of [[Shamhat (fate)|]] after she civilized them as a tribute to her. They are canonically [[1other|genderless]], but often [[genderswap (otm)|portrayed as male]] in fanworks. In [[Sensha Otoko]], she is canonically [[genderswap (otf)|]]ped into a girl.

They have been nicknamed "best clay" or "claybae" by fans (a variant of "best girl") as a reference to their origins.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Morii Shizuki]]
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Kobayashi Yuu]]

title: roland_(fate)
body:
Saber-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]], first briefly seen during [[Astolfo (fate)|]]'s Interlude and later made playable during the release of [[Traum (fate/grand order)|]]. He is infamous for an incident where he was rejected by a woman, so he threw off his clothes and ran around [[nude]]. Astolfo [[crossdressing|dressed as a woman]] to appease and calm him down.

He wields the sword [[Durandal (fate)|]]. [[Hector (fate)|]] is his ancestor, and his cousins include Astolfo, [[Bradamante (fate)|]], and Rinaldo.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Sakamoto Mineji]]
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Terashima Takuma]]

title: katsushika_hokusai_(fate)
body:
Foreigner-Class servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. A famous Japanese artist. Some of his more prominent works include the [[kanagawa okinami ura|Great Wave off Kanagawa]] (part of the Thirty-six Views of Mount Fuji), and the first known portrayal of tentacle porn, [[the Dream of the Fisherman's Wife]], among others.

Similarly to [[Artemis (fate)|]] and [[Orion (Bear) (fate)|Orion]], the girl who is summoned is not actually Hokusai; the small black [[octopus]] following her is the [[Toto-sama (fate)|true Hokusai]], while she herself is his daughter "Katsushika Oei":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katsushika_%C5%8Ci], who served as her father's assistant and even produced some works under his name. He takes over her body upon reaching ascension 3, giving her an octopus-themed costume and a purple color scheme.

They have a [[katsushika hokusai (swimsuit saber) (fate)|Swimsuit Saber]] variant, introduced for the summer 2019 event.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Kuroboshi Kouhaku]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Yukana]] (Katsushika Oei)

title: medea_(caster)_(fate)
body:
A character from [[Fate/stay night]], [[Fate/hollow ataraxia]], and [[Fate/Grand Order]]. She has [[blue eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair]], with a [[side braid]] tied behind her left ear. She also has [[pointy ears]].

She is often seen wearing a black [[hood]]ed [[robe]] over a [[purple dress]] while wielding a [[staff]]. Her Noble Phantasm is [[Rule breaker (fate)|]], a [[knife]] with a zig-zagging blade that destroys magical contracts. In [[Fate/hollow ataraxia]], she’s wearing her [[medea (casual wear) (fate)|casual outfit]], which is a [[denim jacket]] over a [[black shirt]] and [[long skirt]].

[[Circe (fate)|]] is her aunt.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]
[b]Illustrator:[/b] [[Nekotawawa]] ([[Fate/Grand Order]])

title: antonio_salieri_(fate)
body:
Avenger-class Servant seen in [[Fate/Grand Order]], first seen during the [[Anastasia (Lostbelt) (fate/grand order)|Russia Lostbelt]].

A composer who was the target of accusations concerning the death of [[wolfgang amadeus mozart (fate)|Mozart]], although there is no actual evidence of murder. Thus, Salieri is classified as an Innocent Monster. He doesn't call himself 'Salieri', but rather the 'Man in Grey' since this Servant is a personification of the concept of 'Mozart's murderer', a supposedly jealous man who took away God's gift to the world of music.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[PFALZ]]
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Seki Toshihiko]]

title: cielo_(nikke)
body:
A character from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]]. She is a member of [[Over the Horizon (nikke)|]] along with [[Sky (Nikke)|]] and [[Sora (Nikke)|]], the Ark's aeronautical squad.

Cielo is a [[flight attendant|stewardess]] and flight instructor for the squad.

Cielo has [[long hair|long]] [[parted hair|parted]] [[blonde hair]], [[yellow eyes]] and [[large breasts]]. She wears a [[blue jacket]] with a [[lapel pin|pin]] on the right [[lapels|lapel]], a [[white shirt]], [[white scarf]], a [[blue hat|blue]] [[garrison cap]], [[white gloves]], a [[blue skirt|blue]] [[pencil skirt]] with a [[side slit]], [[black pantyhose|black]] [[thighband pantyhose]] and a pair of [[black shoes|black]] [[high heels]]. She has an [[earpiece]] in her right ear, a [[walkie-talkie]] and a [[thigh strap]] with a [[thigh holster|holster]] on her left leg.

title: yamanami_keisuke_(fate)
body:
[[Fate/Grand Order]]’s depiction of Yamanami Keisuke, the general-secretary of the [[Shinsengumi]]. He was part of the assassination of [[Serizawa Kamo (fate)|]] and became the organization's second-in-command after Kondou Isami took over until he deserted for unclear reason and committed [[seppuku]] once he was detained, after which [[Hijikata Toshizou (fate)|]] replaced him. 

Originally introduced as an NPC in the [[GUDAGUDA Yamatai-koku]] event, then became summonable as a Saber-class Servant in the [[GUDAGUDA Shin Yamatai-koku]] event.

A Normal-type Legendary [[pokemon (creature)|Pokémon]], #0486 in the National Pokédex.

A gigantic, white [[golem]] with black stripes and gold attachments on its body. Has [[moss]] growing on its shoulders and feet, six round markings on its sides, and a pattern of seven small dots on its "face."

It is the creator of five other Pokémon: [[Regirock]], [[Regice]], [[Registeel]], [[Regieleki]], and [[Regidrago]].

title: gray_(fate)
body:
[[Fate (series)|Fate series]] character. One of the main characters in [[Lord El-Melloi II Case Files]]. In [[Fate/Grand Order]], she is summonable as a Assassin-class Servant.

She is an assistant of [[Lord El-Melloi II]] at the Mage's Association's Clock Tower. She first met Lord El-Melloi II when he arrived in her hometown. She became his apprentice, and was admitted to the Clock Tower of London.

She has a striking resemblance to [[Saber (fate)|]], which Lord El-Melloi II believes is because she's a distant descendant of King Arthur. Her face brings unpleasant memories of the Fourth Holy Grail War for him, so he tells her to wear a hood to hide her face.

Gray has possession of the Noble Phantasm [[Rhongomyniad (fate)|]], the holy lance of King Arthur, that has been passed down through the generations by preserving its mystery through a similar manner to the Tradition Carrier trait held by the Fraga family.

Gray also possess a unique Mystic Code called [[Add (fate)|]].

She is about 15 years old in the events of Adra Castle Case. She is 18 during [[The Adventures Of Lord El-Melloi II]] but looks the same, as she stopped aging after Saber was summoned again in 2004. In [[Fate/strange fake]], she appears in her early twenties. In [[Fate/Grand Order]], she's introduced as an Assassin-class Servant in the [i]Case Files[/i] collaboration event.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Sakamoto Mineji]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Ueda Reina]]

title: china_tracksuit
body:
A standard-issued [[track suit]] used by various [[China|Chinese]] schools, most prominently during the 2000-2010s.

Actor "Wu Jing":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wu_Jing_(actor)] played a physical education teacher in 2019 movie Song of Youth wearing a [[green track suit|green tracksuit]] with "China" (中国) in giant characters. Wu Jing has been the lead actor for several patriotic-themed action movies, and a screenshot of him wearing a green tracksuit with China in giant characters has become one of the hottest memes on the Chinese internet in 2021. There's even a term for memes featuring Wu Jing, called "Jing Memes" (京图).

The meme has further spread after people started photoshopping words onto that screenshot, forming phrases with the word "China" (or "Chinese" depending on the context) in it. "Such as":https://view.inews.qq.com/k/20210417A045LC00 "Mosquitoes fk off of CHINA" and "Failed to lose weight, I blame CHINESE food for being too delicious". Especially during the [[2020 summer olympics|Tokyo Olympics]], where the meme had a blast on "Olympic related edits":https://twitter.com/dramapotatoes/status/1418876451496071168.

[[Genshin Impact]] did a [[parody]] "of this":https://www.superpixel.com/article/24660/genshin-impact-selling-meme-inspired-jacket with a short film in August 2021 featuring an actor wearing a sports jacket with "Liyue" (the nation in Genshin that's based on China) written on it. They also later started to sell merch of this tracksuit.

title: we're_rehearsing_(meme)
body: A [[meme]] on the Chinese internet originating from this "video":[https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1hw411N7fn]. In which a man catches a woman and another man in bed, yet they claim that they're "rehearsing". The man then [[lifting covers|lifts up the their covers]], and somehow sees two extra people lying on the bed and all of them holding instruments.

title: expo2025
body:
A World Expo held in [[Osaka_(city)|]], Kansai, Japan.

"The logo":[https://www.expo2025.or.jp/en/overview/logomark/], nicknamed "inochi-no-kagayaki" and created by graphic designer Shimada Tamotsu, has become a talking point on Japanese Twitter due to its mascot-like, albeit [[eldritch abomination|eldritch]], design. This contrasts the other "top five entries":[https://www.expo2025.or.jp/en/news/news-20200825/] which were more abstract and stereotypical of a logo. This has spawned parodies interpreting the logo in a variety of ways, ranging from cute mascot to clothing motif to horrifying monster.

A mascot character based on the aforementioned logo was also created, which was "named":[https://twitter.com/expo2025japan/status/1549008586218655745] [[MYAKU-MYAKU]].

h4. Further reading:
* "Osaka Chooses Googly-Eyed Logo for Expo 2025 and It’s an Obvious Choice (Spoon & Tamago)":[https://web.archive.org/web/20210619023029/https://spoon-tamago.com/2020/08/25/osaka-expo-2025-logo/]
* "The logo for Osaka's Expo 2025 has been revealed – and it's a little surreal (TimeOut)":[https://www.timeout.com/tokyo/news/the-logo-for-osakas-expo-2025-has-been-revealed-and-its-a-little-surreal-082520]

h4. See also

title: event_follow-up
body:
A chain of illustrations following the progress of an event, usually the release of an anime. The opposite of [[countdown]] illustrations. For animes, these often follow the release of each individual episode. Might be followed by an [[ending celebration]].

These illustrations should always be parented or pooled.

For a single standalone illustration celebrating the generic release of the series, use [[release celebration]] instead.

Often [[second-party source|posted]] by [[official art|official]] accounts or official artists as a way of [[promotional art|promotion]].

h4. Chronological order

* [[announcement celebration]]
* [[countdown]]
* [[release celebration]]

title: komitee_fuer_reichssicherheit
body:
Holy Roman Empire Security Committee (German: Komitee für Reichssicherheit), also known as the Holy Roman National Security Committee, abbreviated as KfR, was the intelligence agency of the [b][[Holy Roman Empire_(chronicle of myers)|]] [/b] from its restoration in 2045 until the establishment of the Terran Republic in 2150. Its organizational structure was similar to the 20th-century Soviet Committee for State Security (KGB), but it was under the jurisdiction of the [[Holy Roman Government]].

== Members ==
(Information classified)

== Trivia ==

In the Russian version of [[Chronicle of Myers]] (titled История Майерса / Istoriya Mayyersa), the Holy Roman Empire Security Committee is referred to as Комитет имперской безопасности / Komitet imperskoy bezopasnosti, abbreviated as КИБ / KIB.

title: chronicle_of_myers

The [b]Chronicle of Myers[/b] series (also known as Myers Mythology, or [i]Ogiverse[/i]) is a Chinese-language online series created by [[Jo Shin Ogi]], broadly labeled on Danbooru under the title of the first work in the series, Chronicle of Myers. Most information about the series is only available in Chinese, whether it be the works contained within or encyclopedic. Uses elements from [[World of Warcraft]], such as the [[Death Knight (Warcraft)|]], the [[Forsaken (World of Warcraft)|]], etc.

Below are linked articles from the Chinese Ogiverse Wikia on each of the works under Myers. Myers can be mistranslated as Miles.

title: stellus_keirich
body:
[b]Takeyama Hoshi[/b], born [b]Stellus Keirich[/b], is a character from [[Jo Shin Ogi]]'s [[Chronicle of Myers]], appearing in [i]Invasion to Shadowlands[/i], [i]Keirichslied[/i] and [i]Vater des Sterns[/i]. An Austrian-Japanese idol, guitarist and vocalist, she is the daughter of [[Albert Keirich]], and the first LGBTQ+ character in the series. Her alias is Hoshino Taichi (星野太一).

She has a wife, [[Hoshino Ryoko (Chronicle of Myers)|]], both members of the group HOSIBOSI. and parents of [[Hoshino Atsuko (Chronicle of Myers)|]] (later Hoshino Kadosada), mentor, manager and producer of [[Shibatou Atsumi]] .

She's the first [[World of Warcraft]]-style [[Death Knight (warcraft)|]] character from [[Chronicle of Myers]].

[spoilers]Born a man, Stellus was condemned dead at birth, but his father, Albert Keirich, could not bear his death. In order to change the situation, Albert resurrected him with magical music. But it came at a price... the dead Stellus opened his eyes after being resurrected, but the magic had forcibly turned him [[undead|into a woman]].

When trying to tagging Stellus, [[1girl]] is commonly used, but if it is based on gender at birth or soul form, it can be [[1boy]], [[old man]], and [[ghost]].
[/spoilers]

Stellus is inspired in part by [[Hoshino Aquamarine]] and [[hoshino ruby|Ruby]] (Aqua: 2/4, Ruby: 2/4, unisex, but idol form is Aqua: 1/4 and Ruby: 3/4), the children of [[Hoshino Ai]] in [[Oshi no Ko]], [[Hoshikawa Lily]] (born gender, but stellus stay on the male identity) in [[Zombie Land Saga]], and [[Darion Mograine]] (both are [[Death Knight (warcraft)|]]) in [[World of Warcraft]].

and Stellus is the Blood Death Knight.

h4. External links

* "Ogiverse Wiki: Stellus Keirich":[http://ogiverse.fandom.com/zh/wiki/斯泰鲁斯·凯利希]

title: albert_keirich
body:
[quote]Luckily, I made my debut in Japan. In order to better embrace my Japanese identity, I changed my name to Atsumi Takeyama. But if I make my debut in Korea and want Koreans to accept me, then I won't be called "Atsumi Takeyama", but "Park Jangmi".
-Albert Keirich[/quote]

Albert Keirich is a character from [[Jo Shin Ogi]]'s [[Chronicle of Myers]]. Born in Vienna in Lower Austria, after naturalization in Japan, he changed his name to Takeyama Atsumi. Founder and center of the famous rock group ATSSOL. The sixth Chancellor of the [[Holy Roman Empire (Chronicle of Myers)|Holy Roman Reich]] after its restoration. He is protagonist of "Keirichslied".

It is said that Keirich's rock style is somewhat close to that of John Lennon.

He is the father of Takeyama Ai and [[Stellus Keirich|Takeyama Hoshi]], and has lived as [[Shibatou Atsumi]].

h6. Trivia
* Some of Keirich's service in the Knights is a reference to real-life Korean stars who have partially served in the military, such as G-DRAGON.
* Keirich dislikes being called a "sound nerd" or a "noisemaker" the most.
* Keirich has dual German and Austrian citizenship (because his birthplace of Vienna is part of the Austrian region until after 2045, when Keirich renounced his Holy Roman citizenship and became a Japanese citizen and changed his name to Atsumi Takeyama), but after the re-establishment of the Holy Roman Reich, he even rocked the national anthem of the Holy Roman Republic "Kaiserhymne" in the capital Rome, which was appreciated by the Holy Roman Kaiser [[George Myers|George I]]. He was naturalized as a Japanese citizen after the end of World War III.
* Keirich's music genre is J-POP.
* Keirich is a music-game player.
* Keirich's date of birth is March 13, which is the same time as the Anschluss.
* Some of Keirich's early settings are similar to those of the ''[[Love Live!]]'' series characters [[Kosaka Honoka]] (personality), [[Shibuya Kanon]] (guitar), and [[Wien Margarete]] (Austrian nationality), but Keirich and Honoka share the same color and hair color.
* Some of Keirich's later settings are references to Hoshino Ai from Oshi no Ko.
* [spoilers]Keirich was the only Holy Roman Chancellor to be assassinated, and his death was very similar to that of the third presidents of the Republic of Korea, Park Chung-hee and John Lennon and [[Hoshino Ai (oshi no ko)|]] from ''[[Oshi no Ko]]''.[/spoilers]
* Keirich is not very good at cooking, not to mention that tempura is sometimes made with cheese and sausage.
* Keirich occupies center-position (far right) in the poster for the 2057 ATSSOL concert in London, similar to [[John Lennon]] on the album cover of [[Abbey Road]] in reality.

h4. External links

* "Ogiverse Wiki: Albert Keirich":[http://ogiverse.fandom.com/zh/wiki/阿尔伯特·凯利希]
other_names: アルベルト・カイリヒ

title: team_spica's_trainer
body:
Team Spica's [[trainer (umamusume)|]] from the anime version of [[Umamusume|Umamusume]]. 

Appears as a young man with [[brown hair]] done in a [[short ponytail]] with shaved [[undercut]]s at the left and back sides of his head. He has [[yellow eyes]] and wears a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[yellow shirt|yellow]] [[collared shirt|collared]] shirt under a [[black vest]]. He also wears dark-colored [[pants]].

Team Spica's trainer is currently unnamed. He is often nicknamed "Okino T" by the Japanese fanbase, as a reference to his seiyuu, [[Okino Kouji]]. The Trainer also shares some resemblance with his seiyuu.

He is sloppy at his job and often teases [[Toujou Hana|Hana]] in their rivalry. His careless behavior often results in him getting bullied by his own pupils. Instead of properly instructing his pupils with racing strategies, he trusts them and allow them to run according to their own desire. However, he can be a little strict on their training. Despite his 'unique' and impulsive ways of managing his team, things do go well. He also can be off-putting upon first meet, he tends to feel horse girl's thigh muscles which lead to misunderstandings.

In an official model sheet, his name is stated as 西崎リョウ (Nishizaki Ryou) though this is never referenced in other published materials.

title: miyayama_yoshiyasu
body:

title: tenzoji_mika_(chronicle_of_myers)
body:
[b]Mika Tenzoji[/b] (original name: Sharirah) is a character appearing in [[Chronicle of Myers|Myers Gaiden: Mystery of Lemuria]]. She is an orange-haired, red-eyed female monk. The character also makes a brief cameo in Vater des Sterns, part of the Keirich Trilogy.

Her name means śarīra in Sanskrit, referring to the jewel-like relics found among the ashes of eminent monks or the Buddha after cremation.

The character can be obtained in two ways: through the limited-time gacha event "Monk of the Transforming Woman" or by purchasing the base edition of Myers Gaiden: Mystery of Lemuria. Purchasing the Collector’s Edition of Mystery of Lemuria additionally grants the exclusive monk-only transmog "Tenzoji Abbot".

title: judgement_armor
body:
Judgement Armor or Judgment Armos is the tier 2 paladin armor set of [[World of Warcraft]].

"The Judgement concept is meant to be an Inquisitor-like outfit. The Silver Hand is an overall noble establishment, to be sure -- but there is a time when pleasantries must end and justice must be done. It is called the Judgement armor for a reason -- it is the Paladin's embodiment of delivering their sentence upon the enemy. This is not the defender aspect of the Paladin you're seeing; it is the commanding, faceless aspect of justice, of judgement. There is more to a Paladin than shining armor."

—Blizzard Community Manager Caydiem

title: forest_fairy_(dungeon_&_fighter)
body:
The [b]Forest Fairy[/b] (Korean: 숲의 요정 [i]supe yojeong[/i]; Chinese: 树丛精灵 [i]shucong jingling[/i]; Japanese: 森の妖精 [i]mori no yousei[/i], lit. "Forest/Wood Elf") is a common mob of [[Dungeon & Fighter|Dungeon Fighter Online]] that appears in the Time Gate dungeon The Great Blaze.

A female member of the Elven race that once inhabited the mystical forest of Grand Flores. Due to a wildfire that broke out within the forest known as the Great Blaze (格兰之火), Grand Flores burned down and the Elves mysteriously disappeared. It is speculated that she along with most of her kin vanished among the flames.

During the Time Gate story arc, Adventurers encounter Forest Fairies while traveling through the first time zone of Time Gate which takes them to Grand Flores prior to the Great Blaze. Initially, the Forest Fairies are indifferent and non-aggressive toward the Adventurers, and view them as outsiders. However, after the wildfire takes place, they indiscriminately attacks all outsiders, believing the Adventurers to be affiliated with the arsonists who started the fire.

title: armsel_striker
body:
The [b]Armsel Striker[/b] is a 12-gauge [b]shotgun[/b] of [[South Africa]]n origin, designed for designed for [[rioting|riot]] control and [[combat shotgun|combat]]. It is also known as Sentinel Arms Co Striker-12, Protecta, Protecta Bulldog and SWD Street Sweeper. The weapon features a top-[[folding stock]], pistol grip, and a [[vertical foregrip]]. The most distinctive feature is its [b]revolving cylinder[/b], that has 12-[[shotgun shell|round]] capacity and 7-round on more compact variants.

It was initially designed by a Rhodesian national, Hilton R. Walker in 1981, who then emigrated to South Africa. He brought his design for the shotgun with him as well. A copy of the Striker was made by the US gunmaker Cobray and marketed as the SWD Street Sweeper from 1989 through 1993.

title: shield_wall
body:
A [[military]] formation common in ancient and medieval warfare where soldiers would stand shoulder-to-shoulder and hold their shields so that they would abut or overlap.  While no longer used in military tactics, today it is still utilized by [[police]] forces, especially in [[rioting|riot]] suppression.

h4. See also

* [[phalanx]]

h4. External links

"Wikipedia: Shield wall":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shield_wall]

title: riot_shield
body:
A modern [b][[shield]][/b] used by [[police]] and some [[military|armed forces]] in riot control to protect the shield carrier from melee attacks and also thrown projectiles, or non-lethal weapons such as rubber bullets and water cannons.
Riot shields are typically made out of transparent polycarbonate and are designed to be shatter resistant, but are generally not ballistic resistant.

Riot shields can either come in two main variants, one that is one-handed that affords less protection but allows the user to use the other arm, generally to wield a baton. It has two handles, the left-most of which is held on to while the other keeps the arm in place. And another that requires both arms and provides full protection.

[b]Not to be confused[/b] with [[ballistic shield]] which is identifiable by its opaque, often metallic appearance and with narrow viewing port.

title: riot_police
body:
Heavily armored [[police]] officers who are called during situations that would present a high risk of danger to the standard police force, such as [[mob]]s, [[rioting|riots]], and other large scale, or potentially highly dangerous small scale events or operations. Often they are called to provide containment or potentially pacify violence.

Commonly depicted with black armor, transparent [[riot shield]]s, and [[face shield|visored]] [[riot helmet|helmet]]s.

title: roman_fyodorovich_von_ungern-sternberg
body: A russian warlord who lead russia asiatic cavalry forces during ww1 and russian civil war. But he was known for being crazy esoteric buddhist madman who thought he was descendant of genghis khan and went on to take over mongolia for a while. In mongolia, he was known as national hero because he beat chinese army who wanted to reclaim mongolia once more after the country become independent following the collapse of qing dynasty.

title: big_belly
body:
A [[stomach]] that is noticeably large, as if decisively full, [[fat]], or [[pregnant]]. Commonly used when depicting a character that has eaten a great deal of food ([[bloated]]). Not necessary when depicting [[pregnant|pregnancy]] unless the character's belly is very large even in spite of their current condition. Can be used in indecisive cases where it's not clear if the character is actually pregnant.

For a [[midriff]] that is only somewhat [[plump]] or flabby, use [[belly]] instead. Avoid using both [[belly]] and [[big belly]], as they generally do not overlap.

h4. See Also

* [[fat]]
* [[plump]]
* [[belly]]
* [[pregnant]]
* [[inflation]]

title: magical_mirai_miku_(2013)
body:
The 2013 [[Magical Mirai (Vocaloid)|]] version of [[Hatsune Miku]], illustrated by [[chris4708|CHRIS]].

She is the first Magical Mirai version and as such has a magician theme with a [[top hat]] and [[wand]]. Her outfit consists of [[white gloves]], [[black jacket]], [[blue dress]], and [[knee boots]].

She did not initially have a theme song like all later [[Magical Mirai Miku]]s. However, for the 10th anniversary of Magical Mirai in 2023, the song [[Invitation! (vocaloid)|]] by Negi ShowerP was released in commemoration and can be considered her de facto theme song.

title: shi_huang_di_(concept_design)_(fate)
body:
[[Azuma Toh]]'s original concept design for [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Shi Huang Di (fate)|]], seen in post #3338439. Quoting Toh, she said, "On a side note, when I first received the offer to draw Qin, I had imagined he would be a man with an intelligent sharp eyed look as illustrated below based on his previous descriptions. However the design order was a 'fully-naked androgynous fantastical beauty', so this was rejected within an hour."

Toh's original design for Shi Huang Di has him more in his mid-30s to early 40s, possessing a mustache, hair tubes for his sidelocks, wearing a [[mian guan]], and a robe with intricate patterns on the collar.

title: scathach_(fate)
body:
A Heroic Spirit in [[Fate/Grand Order]] also appearing in [[Fate/Extella Link]]. The Witch of Dun Scaith. She was the teacher of [[Cu Chulainn (fate/stay night)|]] from [[Fate/Stay Night]].

She has [[very long hair]] that is desaturated reddish magenta but often perceived to be [[purple hair|purple]], and [[red eyes]], and wears a purple [[bodysuit]]. Like [[Cu Chulainn (fate/stay night)|]], she wields the [[spear]] [[Gae Bolg (fate)|]], and dual-wields them for her Noble Phantasm, the [i]"Gae Bolg Alternative"[/i].

Scathach has a generally calm and somewhat serious personality. However, this does not prevent her from caring about sexual matters, at one point even asking her master to bear their child when they're stuck on an island during the 2016 summer event.

A Caster-class version of her from the [[Gotterdammerung (fate/grand order)|Norse lostbelt]] known as [[Scathach Skadi (Fate)|]] was teased in the trailers for Cosmos in the Lostbelt and released as a playable servant during the game's 3rd anniversary.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Koyama Hirokazu]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Noto Mamiko]]

body:
A character from [[Arknights]]. A Predecessor scientist, [[Doctor (arknights)|]]'s former colleague during the previous civilization, whom he [spoiler]developed and launched the Originium project with[/spoiler], and very likely [spoiler]his lover[/spoiler]. Like Doctor, she lacks any animal traits the Terran people possess. She has made several appearances throughout the story, but they're suspected to only be projections of her by the Originium's Assimilated Universe, her consciousness seems to be somewhere within the Assimilated Universe. Her real state remains unclear.

Priestess has [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[brown hair]] and [[purple eyes]], and is usually portrayed wearing a lab coat, a white shirt with a black ribbon tied around her neck underneath, and a black skirt.
other_names: プリースティス(アークナイツ)

title: mysterious_heroine_x_(fate)
body:
Yet another version of [[Artoria Pendragon (fate)|]], this time summoned as the Assassin Class. Wears a [[scarf]], [[blue jacket|blue]] [[track jacket]], [[shorts]], and a [[baseball cap]] that somehow [[hair through headwear|fails to conceal]] Artoria's iconic [[ahoge]].

She appears in the Type-Moon [[April Fools]] joke [[Rojiura Satsuki: Chapter Heroine Sanctuary]], [[Fate/Grand Order]] and [[Fate/EXTELLA]].

Her goal is to rid the universe of the ever growing Artorias and their ilk as she considers them a plague upon the universe and once they are gone she shall be the one and only Artoria. Although primarily focused on her mission to exterminate all Artorias, she has opened her heart to [[Saber Lily]].

Consequently, Artoria wears Mysterious Heroine X's outfit as an alternate costume in [[Fate/EXTELLA]].

Wields the mysterious magical sword, the [[Himitsucalibur (fate)|]]. Its capabilities and powers are a secret.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]
[b]Illustrator:[/b] [[BUNBUN]] ([[Fate/Grand Order]])
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Kawasumi Ayako]]

title: merlin_(fate)
body:
A minor character in [[Fate/stay night]] and a Caster-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]], first briefly appearing in the [[E Pluribus Unum (fate/grand order)|]] Singularity before being featured in the [[Babylonia (fate/grand order)|]] Singularity.

The wizard from Arthurian legend who helped [[Artoria Pendragon (fate)|King Arthur]] throughout life. An immortal half-incubus sealed within the Reverse Side of the World in the [[Garden of Avalon]], who is usually unsummonable as a Heroic Spirit under normal circumstances. He was the original owner of [[Fou (fate)|]], who hates him.

For the female version from [[Fate/Prototype]], see [[Merlin (Fate/Prototype)]].

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Taiki (luster)|]]
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Takahiro Sakurai]]

title: mikeneko_(vtuber)
body:
A Japanese streamer. An [[indie utaite|independent]] [[utaite]] active from 2011 to 2017, came back in 2022 as an [[indie virtual youtuber|indie]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]].

On 24 April 2022, she officially debuted as a virtual YouTuber.

She joined [[VOICE-ORE]] in July 2023 under the alias Koito Ria until the group was disbanded on June 30, 2024.

She was supposed to debut as a musical artist under [[Pony Canyon]] in 2024 but those plans were cancelled on April 30, 2024.

title: self_cosplay
body:
A character's variant [[cosplay|wearing the clothes]] of another variant of their own, such as a [[magical girl]]'s civilian identity wearing her magical girl identity's clothes. The [[Precure]] franchise has an unofficial term for this, which is "midform".

It's usually one of the following scenarios:
* The outfit doesn't match with the wearer's current hairstyle
* The outfit doesn't match with the wearer current hair color, eye color, scars, personality, etc.
* The outfit belongs to a younger version but the wearer has an older body, or vice versa

Similar to [[fusion]] and [[split theme]], but instead of merging, the character looks more like they simply changed clothes.

If instead, the hairstyle doesn't match the state of the body, it might be a [[self-borrowed hairstyle]].

title: self-borrowed_hairstyle
body:
A character's variant [[borrowed hairstyle|wearing the hairstyle]] of another variant of their own.

To distinguish from general [[self cosplay]]s, it must be clear that the hairstyle doesn't belong to the wearer's current body. Such as:

* The hairstyle's original hair color is different from the wearer's current hair color
* The hairstyle belongs to a younger version but the wearer has an older body, or vice versa
* Other mismatched traits such as eye color, scars, personality etc.

title: impid_(rimworld)
body: Impids are a xenotype of fire-breathing devilish desertpeople. They are adapted well to the desert, but sacrifice ability with melee fighting, plants, and animals, to accomplish this. They're recognizable by their horns, bright skin, and fire-breathing attacks.

title: castlevania_(series)
body:
A side-scrolling platformer video game series by [[Konami]], known in Japan as 悪魔城ドラキュラ ([i]Akumajou Dracula[/i], lit. [i]Devil's Castle Dracula[/i]).

The player typically controls one character at a time, often of the Belmont clan, in a journey through [[Dracula (castlevania)|]]'s demon castle, Castlevania, to defeat him and his hordes.

The series was originally a straightforward, level-based 2D platformer, but with the release of the PlayStation entry [[Castlevania: Symphony of the Night]], the formula became more adventure-based and exploration-focused (to the point of being [[Metroid]]-like, coining the term "Metroidvania") and subsequently a hit, with most subsequent entries following its build.

title: purinnishiteyaruno_(racehorse)
body:
[[Real life|Real-life]] Japanese thoroughbred racehorse. Sired by [[Daiwa Major (racehorse)|]] ([[Daiwa Scarlet (racehorse)|]]'s half-brother) and foaled by C Karma (from Exchange Rate). Named after the catchphrase of a certain [[Miyako (princess_connect!)|pudding-loving ghost]] from [[Princess Connect!]]. Yes, [i]seriously[/i].

She had a career record of two wins from 31 races, lasting from June 2020 until her untimely death in January 2023 (her last race being on the 22nd).

Her name literally means "I'm gonna turn you into pudding!"

h4. External links

* "JBIS: Purinnishiteyaruno":[https://www.jbis.jp/horse/0001268936/]

title: hiker_(pokemon)
body:
A recurring Trainer class in the [[pokemon|Pokémon]] series. They typically appear as [[fat|large]], usually [[beard]]ed men carrying a [[hiking pole]] and wearing hiking gear, often including a large [[backpack]]. In [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]], [[pokemon usum|Ultra Sun and Moon]], and [[pokemon swsh|Sword and Shield]], they are depicted as younger and more [[toned]] compared to previous incarnations. In [[pokemon sv|Scarlet and Violet]], they are depicted as [[muscular]] [[muscular female|women]].

title: tachie_(fate)
body:
A heroine of [[Fate/stay night]] introduced in Fate/unpublished material and Shielder-class Servant of Ernest Gravehill.

Known as the Stray Servant (はぐれ サーヴァント), she was a heroine candidate during the development of [[Fate/stay night]] who was left unused in the final version. She was considered along with [[medusa_(fate)|Rider]] and [[medea (caster) (fate)|Caster]] to be a possible heroine, but she was cut due to the plot beginning to stray so as to keep it manageable for the player. As [[artoria_pendragon_(fate)|Saber]] is a "Servant of the Sword", she was to be her rival as a Shielder, "Servant of the Shield."

The design was later revived for [[Fate/Grand Order]] in 2015 for Kinoko Nasu to allow her to be one of the main heroines along with [[artoria_pendragon_(fate)|Saber]] and [[jeanne_d'arc_(fate)|Ruler]], thus becoming [[Mash Kyrielight]]. She is featured in the doujin game [[Fate/Empire of Dirt]].

title: kamikita_komari
body:
A character of [[Little Busters!]].

Has great interest in fairy-tales, picture books, candy, and clothing with many layers of frills. She is very clumsy, and will often not think before she acts. She does well in her studies and is also surprisingly athletic, though this is somewhat hampered by the fact that she is quite weak and has never done any sport properly before.

title: pioneer_neckerchief
body:
The traditional [[red neckerchief]] worn by someone in the [[Pioneer movement]], adapted from the [[Scout uniform]]. Known in East Asia as the "red neckerchief".

Can also be found as part of the Girls' [[Soviet School Uniform]].

title: scythe
body:
A traditional long handled agricultural tool used to harvest whole plants, such as hemp or wheat. Commonly depicted as a weapon of choice used by the [[grim reaper]] as a tool to reap souls, or by other mythological beings. 

Although often seen in fantasy and anime as a [[weapon]], it is only tangentially connected to the "war scythe", which is a [[polearm]] having more in common with a [[glaive (polearm)|]], fauchard or [[naginata]] than with the original tool.

h4. See also

* [[sickle]]
* [[kama (weapon)]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Scythe":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scythe]

title: team_31a_(heaven_burns_red)
body:
Team 31A (or Squad 31A) is the main team in [[Heaven Burns Red]]. It consists of [[Kayamori Ruka]], [[Izumi Yuki (Heaven Burns Red)|]], [[Aikawa Megumi]], [[Toujou Tsukasa]], [[Asakura Karen (Heaven Burns Red)|]] and [[Kunimi Tama]].

They also perform as the main members of in-universe band She is Legend, with Ruka on [[singing|lead vocals]] and [[guitar]], Karen on co-lead vocals and screams (the latter if her Karen-chan persona takes over), Megumi on guitar, Tama on [[bass guitar|bass]], Tsukasa on [[keyboard (instrument)|]] and Yuki on [[drum set|drums]].

title: harp
body:
A string [[instrument]] having an upright triangular frame consisting of a pillar, a curved neck, and a hollow back containing the sounding board, with strings of graded lengths that are played by plucking with the fingers.

Related to but distinct from the [[lyre]], which is smaller, played while being picked up by the player, and often U-shaped.

title: arcana_(nikke)
body:
A playable character from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]]. A member of the [[Best Seller (nikke)|]] squad, along with [[Phantom (nikke)|]].
 
She is an extrovert through and through, with a friendly personality that makes her able to get along with just about anyone.

She also runs a small [[tarot]] shop as a side business. Her proclivity for eccentricity is channeled into her unique interpretations of tarot cards, which she then uses to tease others (mostly the [[Commander (nikke)|]]). Her readings tend to be surprisingly accurate, so her shop was quite successful.

Illustrator: [[tigerMtang]] 
Voice actress: [[Skyler Davenport]] (EN), [[Murakami Natsumi (voice actor)|]] (JP)

title: kotomine_kirei
body:
A character from [[Fate/stay night]]. He is a [[priest]] that oversees the 5th Holy Grail War.

In [[Fate/stay night]], Kotomine is in his mid 30's with slightly long [[brown hair]] and blank [[brown eyes]]. He wears a black bishop class priest uniform with, usually opened, dark purple [[cassock]] with golden [[cross]]. In [[Fate/Zero]], during his younger days he was in his mid 20's, he had short [[brown hair]] and wore a lower class habit.

Kotomine is often associated with [[mapo tofu]] and this is sometimes used as a reference to him (a fan nickname for him is "Mapo Priest").

title: kotomine_kirei_(businessman)
body:
The version of [[Kotomine Kirei]] seen in [[Fate/Tiger Colosseum]]. In this universe, he loses his memories and is tricked into becoming a businessman. He eventually regains his memories and returns to his former self, confronting the one who caused his amnesia.

title: jekyll_and_hyde_(fate)
body:
A Berserker-class appearing in [[Fate/Prototype: Fragments of Blue and Silver]]. He later appears as an Assassin-class servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

[[Henry Jekyll (Fate)|]] is the neat-looking one, while [[Hyde (Fate)|]] has [[red eyes]], [[messy hair]], an unbuttoned vest and a [[blood stain]] on his shirt. They both use a knife in combat.

In [[Fate/Grand Order]], Jekyll starts as an Assassin, and when he changes to Hyde via his Noble Phantasm, he becomes a Berserker.

[b]True Name:[/b] Dr. Henry Jekyll & Mr. Edward Hyde

title: hyde_(fate)
body:
The secondary personality of [[Jekyll and Hyde (fate)|]] that manifests after [[Henry Jekyll (fate)|]] uses his [[Noble Phantasm (fate)|]] [b]Dangerous Game[/b].

In [[Fate/Prototype: Fragments of Blue and Silver]], the transformation results in him appearing as a [[werewolf]]-like creature. After being corrupted by the [[Holy Grail (fate)|]], he becomes the dominant personality and can temporarily maintain a human form for only an hour at a time.

In [[Fate/Grand Order]], the transformation keeps him in a human form, but he switches his class from Assassin to Berserker.

title: kashin_koji_(fate)
body:
Assassin-class Servant introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Fuun Karakuri Illya-jou]] event. She is based on the folklore Japanese figure who supposedly performed magical arts to various historical figures in the Muromachi period. In Fate she appears as an [[android]] who has fully replaced all parts of their physical body and no longer remembers what gender her original body was. When she constructed [[Katou Danzou (fate)|]], she had a male body.

Using her [[Noble Phantasm (fate)|]] [b]Karakuri Gehou[/b] causes her to transform into a "jorougumo":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jorōgumo, a type of spider-like [[traditional youkai|youkai]].

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Yoneyama Mai]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Seto Asami]]

title: hijikata_toshizou_(fate)
body:
Berserker-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]] first appearing in the [[GudaGuda Meiji Ishin]] event. Wears a western-style outfit or a worn kimono and tattered grey Shinsengumi haori. Wields a katana, rifle and revolver in battle, and his Noble Phantasm is "Shinsengumi: Undying Sincerity", a powerful attack that only grows stronger the closer he is to death.

Like the other Shinsengumi servants, Hijikata is often depicted with certain personality from character based on the same figure in [i][[Gintama]][/i]. Specifically [[Hijikata Toushirou]]'s [[mayonnaise]] addiction.

[b]Character Design[/b]: [[Yogo Yuuki]] 
[b]Voice Actor[/b]: [[Hoshino Takanori]]

title: senji_muramasa_(fate)
body:
[quote][i]Convergence is proof of one's ideals.
As you hammer the blade upon the anvil, you burn thyself all the more brightly.[/i][/quote]

[[Fate/Grand Order]] character. An NPC first appearing in [[Shimousa (fate/grand order)|]], he is summoned as a pseudo-Servant using the body of [[Emiya Shirou]], as foreshadowed in the Limited/Zero Over [[Craft Essence (fate)|]].

He is later introduced as a playable Saber-class Servant in the New Years 2021 event. His Noble Phantasm is [b]Tsumukari Muramasa: Originless Creation of Swords.[/b] He also appears as an Alter Ego-class servant in [[Avalon le Fae (fate/grand order)|]] [spoiler]as one of the [[Foreign Disciples (fate/grand order)|]].[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]

title: chaldea_boys_collection
body:
An annual [[White Day]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]] focusing on male (and [[1other|other]]) servants, with new [[craft essence (fate)|]]s and special gacha banners. Depending on the year, this coincides with the release of a new servant or an [[official alternate costume]] for an existing servant. Many craft essences from year to year take place within shared settings, the most notable being the Detective Edmond series (localized as The Dantès Files). Starting in 2019, a limited-time event with story featuring the focus servant would be released alongside the craft essences. Starting in 2022, the craft essences would receive voice lines. h4. title: slapstick_museum
body:
[b]Holy Grail Phantom Thief Amakusa Shirou and the Slapstick Museum[/b]
[quote]Ladies and Gentlemen, thank you all for gathering here today! Tonight's festivities will take place in a wondrous art museum which houses an unrivalled collection of relics of heroes famous the world over, from every era! Security here is second to none, as it is fully staffed by guards, equipped with magical energy detectors, and even boasts a number of Servants safeguarding its many treasures!

But one man has the audacity to attempt to breach this unbreachable museum. Any phantom thief attemptng such an improbable feat must be reckless in the extreme, and most importantly, without a hint of shame! Fittingly, the calling card he leaves behind appears to ridicule the museum's supposedly impenetrable security.

"I am coming for your museum's Holy Grail."

Transforming his favorite sword into a cane, the phantom thief dressed in a black tuxedo steps into the night with a bewitching smile. Please enjoy the one-night only dramatics as the pursuit of the Holy Grail unfolds alongside the resolution of the Singularity![/quote]

A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on March 3, 2021 and on the NA server on March 3, 2023.

title: habetrot_(fate)
body:
Rider-class Servant introduced in the [[Avalon le Fae (fate/grand order)|British Lostbelt]] of [[Fate/Grand Order]]. A fairy from British and Scottish folklore associated with the [[spinning wheel]], who helps make girls into brides. Somewhat of a [[minigirl]], at only 50~60cm (19~24") tall. Often seen alongside [[cat]]s, and is nicknamed Habenyan or Habbycat.

In the British Lostbelt, [spoiler]she was originally a fairy named Totorot allied with [[Aesc (fate)|]] who ended up meeting [[Mash Kyrielight]] when she rayshifted back in time. After Aesc decided to become [[Morgan le Fay (fate)|]], Habetrot ends up guarding Mash Kyrielight's [[Black Barrel (type-moon)|]] inside her spinning wheel while Mash was kept frozen in ice. She hid her identity when meeting Mash again during Chaldea's arrival, and ends up being erased as a time paradox once Mash remembers who she is during the battle against [[Cernunnos (fate)|]].[/spoiler]

She is given as a reward to players upon completing Avalon le Fae. Similarly to event servants, she doesn't change appearance as she ascends. She's often paired up with [[Miss Crane (fate)|]] in official material due to both being servants who sew.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Hirai Yukio]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Itou Ayasa]]

title: gawain_(fate)
body:
[[Fate (series)|Fate series]] character. A Saber-class servant who appears in [[Fate/EXTRA]], [[Fate/EXTRA CCC]], [[Fate/EXTRA CCC Fox Tail]], [[Fate/EXTELLA]], and [[Fate/Grand Order]].

A [[blonde hair]]ed man with [[blue eyes]], he dons [[white armor]] and owns [[Excalibur Galatine (fate)|]]. One of the [[Knights of the Round Table (fate)|]] that appeared in the Arthurian legends. As the son of King Lot and [[Morgan le Fay (fate)|]], his siblings include [[Gareth (fate)|]], [[Agravain (fate)|]], and [[Mordred (fate)|]] (half-sister).

Infamous for his notoriously difficult battle in the [[Camelot (fate/grand order)|]] singularity.

title: edmond_dantes_(fate)
body:
Avenger-class Servant seen in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Notable for being the first Avenger introduced in the game.

Edmond Dantes is the protagonist of [[Alexandre Dumas (fate)|]]' [i]"The Count of Monte Cristo":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Count_of_Monte_Cristo][/i]. Good-natured and innocent in the beginning, he is framed as a supporter of the exiled Napoleon Bonaparte and imprisoned.  In prison he befriends another political prisoner, a priest named Faria, who educates him. Dantes later escapes, and hardened by his experiences, he goes on to create a new identity for himself as the Count of Monte Cristo, and uses his new position to exact revenge on all those who wronged him in the past.

In [[Fate/Grand Order]] he does not consider himself as Dantes at all, rather as the vengeful King of the Cavern.

[b]Character Design[/b]: [[Komatsuzaki Rui]], [[Routo]] ([[The Count of Monte Cristo (fate)|]])

title: captain_nemo_(fate)
body:
Leader of the [[Nemo (fate)|]] series and the captain of the [[Nautilus (fate)|]], first appearing in the [[S I N (fate/grand order)|]] chapter under the alias [b]Captain[/b]. Identifiable by his long [[twintails]] and feathered [[turban]]. Similarly to the servants appearing in the [[Shinjuku (fate/grand order)|]] singularity, he is a Phantom servant summoned by [[Sion Eltnam Sokaris]]. His components are [[Captain Nemo]] and [[Triton]], though he wouldn't reveal his true name until the end of the [[Yugakshetra (fate/grand order)|]] chapter. Starting in the [[Atlantis (fate/grand order)|]] chapter, other members of the Nemo series begin to manifest in Novum Chaldea.

title: jacques_de_molay_(foreigner)_(fate)
body:
Foreigner-class Servant introduced in the [[Halloween Rising!|Halloween 2021 event]] of [[Fate/Grand Order]]. A [[genderswap]]ped version of the 23rd and the last grandmaster of the [[Knights Templar]].

The Foreigner Jacques de Molay is an innocent Heroic Spirit, whose Spirit Origin has been warped and transformed by the scandals and stigma spread by the people in power and the masses who were envious of the Templars. Furthermore, having been possessed by the evil god proclaiming to be the "Holy Mother of the Abyss" that hastens the corruption of mankind, that evil nature has been boosted. Notably turned his body into that of a woman.

It is said that the symbol of the ominous and sinister, "Friday the 13th", comes from the day of the incident when the Templars were simultaneously exposed.

For the original male Saber-class version of Molay, see [[Jacques de Molay (Saber) (fate)|]].

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Kuroboshi Kouhaku]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Aoki Shiki]]

title: manannan_mac_lir_(fate)
body:
Alter Ego-class Servant introduced in the [[Manannan Souvenir Valentine|Valentine 2022 event]] of [[Fate/Grand Order]]. A Pseudo-Servant using [[Bazett Fraga McRemitz]] as his vessel. The Celtic god of the sea and the Otherworld, who owns many magical items such as a self-navigating boat named Sguaba Tuinne, the horse Aonbharr that can cross water, and the mystical sword [[Fragarach (fate)|]].

title: shinonome_akito
body:
A [[Project Sekai]] character. He is [[Shinonome Ena]]'s brother, a student of [[kamiyama high school uniform (project sekai)|Kamiyama High School]] and a member of [[Vivid BAD SQUAD (project sekai)|]]. His voice actor is "Imai Fumiya.":https://projectsekai.fandom.com/wiki/Imai_Fumiya

title: yuki_aine
body:
One of the main characters of [[Aikatsu Friends!]] and an [[idol]]. She enrolls in [[star harmony academy school uniform|Star Harmony Academy]] at the beginning of the series. She's [[Minato Mio]]'s partner in the friend unit named Pure Palette.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[gradient hair]] consisting of the color [[pink hair|pink]] and [[orange hair|orange]] that ends in [[drill hair|drills]] and goes right [[hair over shoulder|over her shoulders]]. She wears a [[blue bow]] in her [[hair bow|hair]] with a [[hairband]], the latter which she ditches in the second season.

[b]Tagging note:[/b] when a post depicts Aine with [[large breasts]], please also include the [[alternate breast size (larger)]] tag, as the size is not canonically accurate. See below for more info.

In the second season of the series (subtitled [i]Kagayaki no Jewel[/i]), fans noticed an unexpected change in Aine's 3D model, which was altered to show a more developed bust. Interestingly, this change is not noticable in the 2D animated parts of the show (she still appears flat even in bikini), and no similar adjustments were made to the body types of other characters (see 3D model comparison "here":https://i.imgur.com/13rS3pk.jpeg). When fans online discovered this, it quickly became a meme, with many fan artists exaggerating Aine's bust size in their illustrations. Aine was also humorously nicknamed ぱいね, a pun combining the words おっぱい ([i]oppai[/i], meaning "breasts") and あいね (Aine).

title: bimbofication
body:
A fetish revolving around a character (particularly female) becoming a "bimbo", i.e. being an often airheaded, hypersexual version of themselves.

Typically, bimbofication involves drawing a character with exaggerated makeup and sexual characteristics, such as [[alternate breast size (larger)|giving them larger breasts]] or [[ass|hips]]. The character's personality is often changed to being fixated on sexual pleasure to various degrees (some retaining their original personality but with more libido, while some are depicted as a stereotypical carefree adulterer).

Bimbofication often stylized the character into a [[gyaru]] and/or [[ganguro]] state of dress in Japanese fetish art, though others simply gave them sexually provocative [[revealing clothes]] and often depicted them as [[prostitution|prostitutes]].

h4. See Also
* [[gyaru]]
* [[ganguro]]
* [[Feminization]]- a similar fetish that often results in a guy becoming hypersexually feminine
* [[Debimbofication (meme)|]]

title: brown_long-eared_bat_(kemono_friends)
body: A [[Kemono Friends]] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park. She first appeared in the original 2015 mobile game, and later appeared in [[Kemono Friends Pavilion]] and [[Kemono Friends 3]] with an updated character design. In these games, she tends to be depicted as an energetic Friend with a good sense of responsibility; this is fairly different from other bat Friends, who tend to be easygoing and/or tricksters. This may be inspired by the brown long-eared bat's unique nature as a species, being a relatively slow-flying and largely diurnal bat. In September 2022, a [[virtual YouTuber]] based on Brown Long-Eared Bat debuted under the franchise's [[Kemono Friends V Project]] label as a member of its second wave, debuting alongside [[Siberian Chipmunk (Kemono Friends)|]] and [[Jungle Cat (Kemono Friends)|]]. KemoV's Brown Long-Eared Bat, commonly addressed by her nickname Usako, is a peppy and humorous girl who enjoys horror games and incorporates verbal tics associated with her [[Kemono Friends 3]] counterpart into her speech. She has a notably different design from her video game counterpart, having [[official alternate hair length|longer hair]] featuring a [[official alternate streak color|pink streak]] and a [[alternate breast size (larger)|dramatically larger chest]] as well as the [[official alternate costume|differing outfit]] that most other KemoV streamers have compared to their inspirations. h4. See also * [[Poporu (kemono friends)|]] h4. External links * "Usako's YouTube channel":https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnyE-wD1pE2GZOxA6OHjW9g * "Usako's Twitter":https://twitter.com/Usako_KEMOV
other_names: ウサギコウモリ(けものフレンズ)

title: sada-chan_(tawawa)
body:
A character from [i][[Getsuyoubi no Tawawa]][/i] that parodies [[Yamamura Sadako]] from [i][[The Ring]][/i]. Her name comes from [[Himura Kiseki]]'s Twitter comments on the character.

Generally resembles Sadako, but with [[alternate breast size (larger)|much bigger breasts]] and apparently far less obsession with killing people, as she ceases to show such tendencies from her second appearance onward in favor of developing a possessive quasi-cohabitative relationship with the boy she's currently haunting.

According to [i]Getsuyoubi no Tawawa Sono VIII[/i], she was a popular child actress but "couldn't get a decent role" and got bullied at school after growing up due to her breast size. She died from accidentally falling into a well because of her heavy breasts during the filming of a low-budget [i]The Ring[/i] parody movie in 1998.

She collected many old game consoles and other electronic products from 1990s in the well like [[Super Famicom]], [[Game Boy]], [[Playstation 1]], [[Tamagotchi]] and Cassette boombox.

She has [[very long hair]], [[bangs]] that obscure her eyes, and wears a white [[robe]]. And as noted above, like other female characters in the series, she has [[large breasts]]. Recently, the author has stated she's the [[huge breasts|largest]] of the current girls.

title: hex_maniac_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Occult Mania[/b] (Japanese), [b]Hex Maniac[/b] (English)

A female-only trainer class in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]][/i] games. While they first debuted in [i][[pokemon_rse|RSE]][/i], their later appearance in [i][[pokemon_xy|XY]][/i] was much more popular. They specialize in Ghost-type and Psychic-type Pokémon.

Occasionally paired with the [[fairy_tale_girl_(pokemon)|Fairy Tale Girl]] due to an in-game trainer pair called the Mysterious Sisters. In [i]XY[/i], a Hex Maniac sells [[Moomoo Milk]].

h5. Appearance

See [[Hex Maniac (Pokemon RSE)]].

h6. [i]Pokémon X, Y, Omega Ruby, and Alpha Sapphire[/i] (Generation VI)

* !post #4993502: Hex Maniac as she appeared in Gen 6 games.

Most fanart is based on their later appearance which debuted in [i][[pokemon_xy|XY]][/i] and later reappeared in [i][[pokemon_oras|ORAS]][/i].

They appear as young [[mojyo|mojyo]] girls wearing a [[long dress|long]] [[black dress]], having [[@_@|swirly manic eyes]], and [[messy hair]] with a [[purple hairband]]. [i]Very[/i] commonly drawn with an [[alternate breast size (larger)|increased cup size]] compared to canon.

title: xu_fu_(fate)
body:
A Servant first seen in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Servant Summer Camp!]] event as an Archer-class NPC. A Chinese alchemist, sorcerer, and explorer who lived from 255 BC to approximately 195-155 BC. [[Shi Huang Di (fate)|]] sent Xu Fu on two separate journeys to find the elixir of immortality.

In Fate, Xu Fu is a woman who was [[yandere|obsessed]] with [[Yu Mei-ren (fate)|]], wanting to also find a way to kill immortals in order to relieve her of her endless life. She is always seen carrying around a [[character doll]] of her.

She appeared in [[Battle in New York 2022]] as [[Odysseus (fate)|Space Odysseus]]'s assistant, [[Space Xu Fu (fate)|]]. She also appears in [[Traum (fate/grand order)|]] as a Caster-class servant of the Righteous Realm, and was introduced as a playable Alter Ego-class servant during the 7th anniversary.

[b]Japanese Reading:[/b] Jo Fuku

body:
Colorful Festival are a type of gacha within [[Project Sekai]] with doubled 4* rates and no ties to any events, usually held on celebratory dates such as New Years or the game's anniversary.
They originally held Permanent cards, but then received Colorful Festival-exclusive cards and costumes.

title: suicide
body:
The act of voluntarily ending one's own life.

The picture must show a character either having already killed themselves or being in the process of doing so.

Also tag [[attempted suicide]] if the person is shown attempting suicide, but fails for some reason (such as another person intervening).

Tag [[imminent suicide]] if the character intends to commit suicide in the imminent future.

title: cs/ls06
body:
The [b]CS/LS06[/b] is a Chinese [[submachine gun]] developed by Chongqing ChangFeng Co. Ltd in the early 1990s. Also known as CS/LS6 or CF-05. Originally designed for 5.8×21mm [[ammunition|cartridge]], it became chambered for 9×19mm Parabellum instead.

The [[weapon]] features a built-in [[vertical foregrip]], a sliding buttstock, and often uses a quick-detachable [[suppressor]]. Its feed system is a top-mounted helical magazine with 50-round capacity.

h4. See also

* [[List of Weapons]] 
* [[CF05 (Girls' Frontline)]]
* [[Zhaohui (Girls' Frontline 2)]] 
* [[Kisaki (Blue Archive)]]

h4. External links

* Wikipedia: "CS/LS6":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CS/LS6

title: lahti-saloranta_m/26
body:
The Lahti-Saloranta M/26 (or LS/26) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [b][[light machine gun]][/b], designed by Aimo Lahti and Arvo Saloranta in 1926. Though often referred as [i]pikakivääri[/i] (automatic [[rifle]]) in Finnish [[military|service]]. The [[weapon]] features a [[barrel shroud]], pistol grip, and [[bipod]]. It predominantly uses standard 20-round [[magazine (weapon)|magazine]].  

h4. See also

* [[List of weapons]]
* [[LS26 (Girls' Frontline)]]
* [[Balthilde (Girls' Frontline 2)]]
* [[Saki (Blue Archive)]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Lahti-Saloranta M/26":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lahti-Saloranta_M/26

title: zenobia_(fate)
body:
Archer-class servant introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Halloween Rising!]] event. The famous warrior queen of the Palmyran kingdom during the crisis of the third century. Well known for her defensive campaign against the Roman emperor Aurelian, whom she eventually fell in love with and married in exchange for sparing her country.

In-game, Zenobia is depicted wearing a black [[bikini]] and a [[g-string]], with her dress being torn down, and being repaired and covering her body in her second and third ascension. According to her lore, the reason for her to wear a scantily-clad costume was because she believed that [[nudist|body exposure is not an indecent act]].

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Nishiide Kengorou]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Shouji Umeka]]

title: yu_mei-ren_(fate)
body:
An Assassin-class Servant appearing in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[brown hair|brown]]-[[black hair]], wears a [[black dress]] and [[dual wielding|wields]] two [[sword]]s. In her unascended form she has a [[braided ponytail]] and wears [[glasses]]. In her ascended form, she removes her glasses and has unbraided hair.

Historically she was known as the lover of [[Xiang Yu (fate)|]]. In Type-Moon lore she is an immortal elemental, a type of spirit similar to the "True Ancestors":http://typemoon.wikia.com/wiki/True_Ancestor like [[Arcueid Brunestud]]. Since she's been ostracized by humans for millennia for being a vampire, she greatly hates mankind. She also deeply despises [[Koyanskaya (fate)|]] because she witnessed "Daji":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daji, another incarnation of the Great Fox, bring down an empire.

[spoilers]As her unascended form indicates, she is the true identity of [[Akuta Hinako]].[/spoilers]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[toi8]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Ise Mariya]]

title: wu_zetian_(fate)
body:
Assassin-class Servant first seen in the [[Agartha (fate/grand order)|]] chapter of [[Fate/Grand Order]] as the [b]Assassin of Nightless City[/b]. The concubine of Emperor Taizong, but after his death, she married his son Gaozong and became Empress following a debilitating stroke that Gaozong suffered. She implemented the short-lived Zhou Dynasty in 690, interrupting the Tang Dynasty until it was abolished in 705 after her death.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Harada Takehito]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Izawa Shiori]]

title: utsumi_erice
body:
Main protagonist of [[Fate/Requiem]], and [[Voyager (fate)|]]'s Master. She is the granddaughter of [[Manazuru Chitose]], and the daughter of an unnamed man and the heroic spirit "Izanami":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Izanami, making her a half-heroic spirit. She works as the "Grim Reaper" in Mosaic City, killing servants who break the rules established by the [[Holy Grail (fate)|]].

She appears in [[Fate/Grand Order]] as a Lancer and Avenger-class Servant.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[NOCO (Adamas)|]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Kitou Akari]]

title: ushiwakamaru_(fate)
body:
A Rider-class Servant, first debuted in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

Typically wears a kanmuri hat, which is tagged as [[tate eboshi]]. Somewhat (in)famous for her [[revealing clothes]] consists of minimal armor plates [[breast curtains|just barely covering]] her [[no bra|bare breasts]] and exposed panties. As such, she is often given a [[black leotard]]-esque undershirt in some later official materials.

[b]True name:[/b] Minamoto no Yoshitsune, one of the most famous warlord from 11th century Japan.
[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Sakamoto Mineji]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Hayami Saori]]

title: stheno_(fate)
body:
Stheno (Greek for "Forceful") is a character from [[Fate/hollow ataraxia]], and can be summoned as an Assassin-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Her Noble Phantasm is "Smile of the Stheno", a powerful debuff and charm against a male opponent.

Has a younger twin sister, [[Euryale (fate)|]], and a younger sister, [[Medusa (rider) (fate)|Medusa]]. Depicted as a [[purple hair]]ed girl with [[purple eyes]], [[twintails]], a [[headdress]] and [[white dress]]. The difference between her sister is the black rose ornament, the slit, and arm decoration is on her left side. They appear identical in Fate/hollow ataraxia.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]], [[Akira (kaned fools)|]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Asakawa Yuu]]

title: okita_souji_(koha-ace)
body:
A [[genderswap]]ped depiction of the [[Okita Souji|Captain]] of the [[Shinsengumi]], she is a Saber-class and Saberface Servant of [[Kohaku (tsukihime)|]] in the TYPE-MOON parody work [[Koha-Ace]] by [[Keikenchi]]. She also appears as a playable character in [[Fate/Grand Order]] and as the servant of [[Akagi Kanata]] in [[Fate/type Redline]].

Her Noble Phantasms are her signature Shinsengumi haori, the Shinsengumi Flag of Sincerity, and Mumyou Sandanzuki. Despite her middling stats and personal skills, she is a force to be reckoned with in the Grand Order conflict.

Okita's running gag within the series revolves around her [[coughing blood]] at any random moment, a reference to her [[real life]] counterpart who suffered from tuberculosis.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Yuuki Aoi]]

title: oberon_(third_ascension)_(fate)
body:
[[Oberon (fate)|]] in his Third Ascension form from [[Fate/Grand Order]]. His hair is [[black hair|black]], and he wears a blue [[diamond hairband]]. He wears a [[white shirt]], [[black pants]], and a large [[black cloak|black]] [[fur-trimmed cloak]] comprised of multiple torn [[fairy wings]]. His right hand remains humanoid, but his left arm turns into a dark [[claws|claw]], and his legs and feet also turn dark. He gains a pair of [[dragonfly wings]], which aren't capable of helping him fly.

[b]Major spoilers for Lostbelt no. 6: Fairy Realm of the Round Table, Avalon le Fay![/b]

[spoiler]This is his true Pretender-class form when he awakens as Oberon Vortigern, the Insect of the Abyss summoned to destroy the British Lostbelt.[/spoiler]

As this ascension is a spoiler for [[Avalon le Fae (fate/grand order)|]], posts that reference his full true name or the events of the Lostbelt finale should also be tagged with [[spoilers]].

title: nitocris_(fate)
body:
A Caster-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]] first appearing in the [[Camelot (fate/grand order)|]] Singularity. The semi-legendary pharaoh of [[ancient Egyptian|ancient Egypt]] known for her legend of her revenge against the conspirator who killed her brother and her depiction in various fictional works as the queen who helds the power of an evil and otherworldly beings. 

She is a [[dark-skinned female]] with [[very long hair|very long]] [[purple hair]] and [[purple eyes]] with [[extra ears|extra]] [[jackal ears]].

title: mochizuki_chiyome_(fate)
body:
Assassin-class servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]] first appearing in [[Shimousa (fate/grand order)|]] as the [b]Assassin of Paraiso[/b]. A legendary founder of the first kunoichi order of her era, she also served as a miko of Orochi, hence her connection to [[Shuten Douji (fate)|]] (who is depicted in Fate/Grand Order as Orochi's daughter).

Usually wears only a [[black ribbon]] with [[fishnets]] (where a part of the ribbon covers her right eye as an [[eyepatch]]), and wields a [[kunai]]. Has [[very long hair|very long]] [[black hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. Often some of her hair [[hair over one eye|covers her right eye]] too. Gains a kunoichi and miko outfit as she ascends, revealing that her covered eye is yellow and has a serpentine pupil, the mark of her priesthood serving Orochi.

[b]Character Design[/b]: [[Hiroyama Hiroshi]]
[b]Voice Actress[/b]: [[Sakura Ayane]]

title: mandricardo_(fate)
body:
Rider-class Servant first seen in the [[Atlantis (fate/grand order)|]] Lostbelt of [[Fate/Grand Order]]. An enemy of the [[Paladins of Charlemagne (fate)|]], but overall a minor character in the stories. He was an adventurer who acquired [[Hector (fate)|]]'s armor and sought [[Durandal (fate)|]], eventually stealing it after [[Roland (fate)|]] threw it away. The version summoned as a servant is him in his mid-thirties from after his adventures, with an extremely jaded personality, who wields a [[wooden sword]] in lieu of Durandal.

title: komahime_(fate)
body:
Berserker-class Servant introduced in the [[GUDAGUDA Shin Yamatai-koku]] event. Komahime was a princess of the Warring States period and the daughter of Mogami Yoshiaki, [i]daimyō[/i] of Dewa. Though she was slated to marry [[Toyotomi Hideyoshi (fate)|]]'s illegitimate child Hideyori, after a proper heir was born in Hidetsugu, Hideyori was sentenced to death and Komahime was executed along with him. Her tragic end at the age of fourteen inspired her father to side against Hideyoshi.

[spoilers]She is the other half of the Servant [[Sen no Rikyu (fate)|]], with her forming the basis of Rikyu's current appearance. The two bonded over their mutual hatred of the Toyotomi clan and, along with the spirits of countless others who shared their grudge, merged together into one Servant. While her personality lies dormant in Rikyu's First and Second Ascensions, she takes over in their Third Ascension.[/spoilers]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Albino (a1b1n0623)|]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Sonozaki Mie]]

title: katou_danzou_(fate)
body:
Assassin-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]] first appearing in the [[Shimousa (fate/grand order)|]] chapter. A ninja master from the Sengoku period, she is depicted here as an [[android]] girl with [[robot joints|robot]] or [[doll joints]] and has a wide variety of attacks at her disposal. She was created by the first Fuuma Kotarou of the Fuuma clan with the help of [[Kashin Koji (fate)|]], and raised the fifth-generation [[Fuuma Kotarou (Fate)|]] as a foster son. Her name is localized as [b]Katou "Black Kite" Danzou[/b] in the English version.

title: kali_(fate)
body:
Alter Ego-class Servant introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Paper Moon (fate/grand order)|]] chapter. One of the two major avatars of the [[Hindu mythology|Hindu]] mother goddess [[Parvati (fate)|]], alongside [[Durga (fate)|]] (represented by her first and second ascension). This form represents Parvati as the "goddess of destruction" and patron goddess of the Durga sect of Hinduism, which participated in various kinds of dark magic and esoteric sacrificial/sexual worshipping. As with her base form, she uses [[Matou Sakura]] as her vessel. As a playable servant, she is an Archer-class.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[starshadowmagician]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Shitaya Noriko]]

title: indra_(fate)
body:
[[Fate (series)|]] character mentioned throughout the franchise but first debuting as a Lancer-class servant with [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Indra no Dai Shiren]] event.

He is the king of gods in the Hindu pantheon and [[Arjuna (fate)|]]'s father. He is known by the name Gozu Tennou in Japan and is the father of [[Minamoto no Raikou (fate)|]]/[[Ushi Gozen (fate)|]] under this name. He was the original wielder of [[Vasavi Shakti (fate)|]], which he gifted to his nephew [[Karna (fate)|]]. He used the [[vajra (object)|]] in order to slay [[Vritra (fate)|]].

As a Lancer-class servant, he manifests the Vajra as a [[Boy Vajra (fate)|young boy]] and [[Girl Vajra (fate)|young girl]]. His [[Indra (third Ascension) (fate)|third ascension]] is locked until players complete the event.

She wears a [[white dress]] that has a black [[see-through cleavage|see-through portion on the chest area]], [[elbow gloves|long]] [[white gloves]], [[black thighhighs]] and a black [[veil]] on her head.

title: euryale_(fate)
body:
Euryale (Greek for "Far-Flier") is a character from [[Fate/hollow ataraxia]], and can be summoned as an Archer-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Her Noble Phantasm is "Eye of the Euryale", a powerful single-target attack that does more damage and charms the target if it is male.

Has an older twin sister, [[Stheno (fate)|]], and a younger sister, [[Medusa (rider) (fate)|Medusa]]. Depicted as a [[purple hair]]ed girl with [[purple eyes]], [[twintails]], a [[headdress]] and [[white dress]]. The difference between her twin sister is the black rose ornament, the slit, and arm decoration is on her right side. They appear identical in Fate/hollow ataraxia.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]], [[Akira (kaned fools)|]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Asakawa Yuu]]

title: emiya_alter
body:
Archer-class Servant first seen in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Shinjuku (fate/grand order)|]] Singularity. The same character as [[Archer (fate)|]], but has discarded his memories after a [[SE.RA.PH (fate/grand order)|tragic incident]] and became an emotionless killer. Emiya Alter has [[very dark skin|darker skin]] than his original version ([[second-party edit|edited]] back to his [[official alternate skin color|original skintone]] in the NA version), and has his hair very short with a [[crew cut]]. He first appeared in [[promotional art]] for Epic of Remnant (post #2635525).

Due to Danbooru's policy of avoiding spoilers as much as possible, as well as simplifying how their costume character tags are categorized, Archer and Emiya Alter are to be treated as wholly separate characters.

For the corrupted version of Archer seen in [[Fate/Grand Order: First Order]], see [[Archer Alter (fate)|]].

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Sasaki Shounen]]
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Suwabe Jun'ichi]]

title: bradamante_(fate)
body:
Lancer-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]], first appearing in the [[Holy Samba Night|2018 Christmas event]]. She is the main heroine of the two Italian epic poems [i]Orlando Innamorato[/i] and [i]Orlando Furioso[/i]. [[Astolfo (fate)|]] and [[Roland (fate)|]] are her [[cousins]].

The animation for her Noble Phantasm became famous among the playerbase (to wit, all her ass-related fanart on Pixiv "has its own tag":[https://www.pixiv.net/tags/プリケツダマンテ/artworks]) for featuring a close-up shot of her [[ass]].

title: bedivere_(fate)
body:
A minor character in [[Fate/stay night]] and a Saber-class servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]] introduced in the [[Camelot (fate/grand order)|]] Singularity. He was one of [[Saber (fate)|]]'s knights of the Round Table. Has a very [[androgynous]] appearance to the point of either being a [[bishounen]] or even a [[trap]]. Is [[amputee|missing his right arm]] and is usually seen wearing a [[prosthetic arm|prosthesis]].

[spoiler]The version appearing in Fate/Grand Order is from a timeline where he never returned [[Excalibur (fate/stay night)|]] to the [[Lady of the Lake]], resulting in [[Artoria Pendragon (fate)|]] being unable to die. He ended up waiting in the Garden of Avalon with [[Merlin (fate)|]] for centuries until the events of the [[Camelot (fate/grand order)|]] singularity, where he was finally able to defeat Artoria, now having been taken over by the holy power of [[Rhongomyniad (fate)|]] and becoming the [[Lion King (lancer) (fate)|Lion King]].[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]
[b]Illustrator:[/b] [[Tenkuu Sphere]] ([[Fate/Grand Order]])
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Noto Mamiko]] ([[Fate/stay night]]), [[Miyano Mamoru]] ([[Fate/Grand Order]])

title: ashiya_douman_(fate)
body:
Alter Ego-class Servant seen in [[Fate/Grand Order]], first introduced in the [[Shimousa (fate/grand order)|]] arc as [b]Caster of Limbo[/b]. Ashiya Douman is best known as the [[onmyouji]] rival of [[Abe no Seimei (fate)|]]. He is one of the [[Foreign Disciples (fate/grand order)|]] helping facilitating the advent of the Alien God.

As an Alter Ego, his component spirits are "Itzpapalotl":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ītzpāpālōtl, "Chernobog":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chernobog_and_Belobog, and [[Akimitsu-dono]]. Perhaps due to Itzpapalotl being a female goddess, Douman's gender is listed as unknown in official material.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Furumi Showichi]]
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Morikawa Toshiyuki]]

title: artoria_pendragon_(lancer_alter)_(fate)
body:
[[Saber (fate)| Artoria Pendragon]] in [[Dark Persona|Alter state]] as a Lancer-class Servant, first debuted in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[London (fate/grand order)|]] Singularity. She uses King Arthur's spear [[Rhongomyniad (fate)|]] instead of [[Excalibur (fate/stay night)|]].

Being based on [[Artoria Pendragon (Lancer) (Fate)|the hypothetical version of]] Artoria who did not possesses the age-halting [[Caliburn (fate)|]] and [[avalon (fate)|Avalon]]. This version of Artoria is [[large breasts|much more developed]] than normal. Battles while mounted on a horse named [[llamrei (fate)|Llamrei]]. Her actions as the Storm King allowed her to head the Wild Hunt after her passing.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Ishida Akira]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Kawasumi Ayako]]

title: arcueid_brunestud
body:
A character from the visual novel [[Tsukihime]], who also makes an appearance in the fighting game [[Melty Blood]] by [[Type-Moon]]. She is voiced by [[Nabatame Hitomi]] in the original Tsukihime anime, by [[Yuzuki Ryouka]] in Melty Blood, and [[Hasegawa Ikumi]] in Type Lumina, the remake, and as [[Archetype_EARTH|Archetype: EARTH]] in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] styled in [[hair intakes]], [[medium breasts|medium]] to [[large breasts]], as well as [[red eyes]]. Her clothing consists of a white [[turtleneck sweater]], a [[long skirt|long]] [[purple skirt]] and [[black pantyhose]]. In the remake, she wears a [[blue skirt|blue]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]] instead along with a silver [[necklace]].

According to multiple sources, Nasu based her design on magazine model Amanda Dyer.
