title: undersuit
body:
When a character is not wearing multiple outer garments that who normally wears, and exposing the inner clothing that is not normally exposed (or partially exposed), but it is not [[underwear only]].
Or the [[undershirt]], [[bodysuit under clothes]], etc. are almost completely exposed with no outer clothes worn.
If the character is simply not wearing one of the outer garments (like [[jacket]], [[cape]], etc), please mainly use no_xx ([[no jacket]], [[no cape]], etc), unless the outer garment usually covers a large area of the inner clothing.

title: goh_(pokemon)
body:
[[Ash Ketchum|Ash]]'s traveling companion in the [[pokemon journeys|Pokémon Journeys: The Series]].

Goh is a book-smart city boy from Vermilion City in Kanto. When he was six, Goh had a fated encounter with [[Mew (pokemon)|]]. Since then, he has dreamed of catching the mythical pokemon. After meeting Ash and travelling to Galar, Goh meets a [[Scorbunny]], and while he initially turns down the enthusiastic Pokémon, it eventually becomes his starter Pokémon. Now, Goh's goal is to fill his Pokédex, believing it will bring him closer to [[Mew (pokemon)|]], rumored to be the common ancestor of all Pokémon.

He has [[dark-skinned male|dark skin]] with [[spiked hair|spiked]] [[black hair]] with [[antenna hair|two ahoges]] sticking out of it. He has [[blue eyes]] and wears dark-colored clothing. Due to the character's [[androgynous]] appearance and a comment by the anime's producer, portraying Goh as a [[trap]] is quite common.

Her [[rigging]] is a split-wing design that holds her three 20.3 cm triple gun mounts on the sides and her two aircraft catapults to her back.

title: kagami_kira
body:
A [[Virtual YouTuber]] and first-generation member of [[Holostars]]. Despite his cute appearance, Kira's conversation topics occasionally veer into perverted territory the most among the Holostars, and he once even conducted a [[cucumber]]-eating [[ASMR]] stream. He normally speaks in a cutesy, effeminate voice, but can drop it by several octaves to the point where it has been described as being similar to [[Kira Yoshikage]] if he wants to. He is a skilled gamer, and usually played [[Apex Legends]] with [[Astel Leda]] and [[Kanade Izuru]]. 

He graduated on November 30, 2020 due to his mental and physical health issues. 

Kira is a [[trap]] who has [[aqua eyes]] and [[messy hair|messy]] [[medium hair|medium]] [[aqua hair]] tied up into a [[twintails]]. His bangs is [[swept bangs|swept]] to the left, and there is an [[ahoge]] on his head. 

His default costume consists of a [[wing collar|wing-collared]] [[sleeveless shirt]] [[crop top]] that exposes his [[midriff]], a [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[aqua skirt|aqua]] [[pleated skirt]] and a [[short necktie]] of the same color and patterns, as well as a [[white coat|white]] [[hooded coat]] decorated with [[pom pom (clothes)|pom pom]] and has [[polka dot]] and plain yellow [[sleeve cuffs]]. He wears [[black thighhighs]] [[platform boots|platform]] [[thigh boots]], a [[black belt]], and a [[plaid hat|plaid]] [[pillbox hat]] with [[rabbit]] and [[heart hat ornament]]. There are several [[hairclip|hairclips]] on his hair and [[brooch|brooches]] on his collar.

title: shimakaze_(kancolle)
body:
[b]Shimakaze[/b] (島風, lit. "Island Wind") is the personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Shimakaze[/i] in [[Kantai Collection]]. 

Shimakaze has [[long_hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[grey eyes]]. She wears a [[crop top|cropped]] [[serafuku]], [[striped thighhighs]], [[white_gloves|white]] [[elbow gloves]], a short [[miniskirt]] with [[black_panties|black]] [[highleg panties]] which show off her [[ass]], and a [[black hairband]] with long floppy "ears". She has small robot familiars called [[Rensouhou-chan]]s which represent her three twin "12.7 cm/50 naval gun":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/12.7_cm/50_Type_3_naval_gun turrets.

h4. Personality and trivia
As she is based on an experimental destroyer built around speed and heavy torpedo armaments, Shimakaze sports a boastful personality, occasionally bragging about how fast she is and nitpick on how "slow" those around her are. In spite of this, due to the historical counterpart only experienced few combat actions (being mostly used as an escort), Shimakaze also have a lazy, "spoiled brat" altitude, being generally carefree and minding her own business rather than the others.

While the historical ship is the fastest bluewater ship in the IJN fleet, she is not the fastest destroyer in the game after the inclusion of [[Tashkent (kancolle)|]] around 2018. After this, Shimakaze is often depicted in fan works as either losing her confidence or viewed Tashkent as a rival she swears to surpass.

Due to her distinctive and revealing outfit, she has become one of the most popular characters of the series, with several artists often drawing the other characters [[cosplay]] [[shimakaze (kancolle) (cosplay)|as her]]. She is also frequently portrayed as a [[trap]] ([[Shimakaze-kun]]) or as an unrelated boy [[crossdressing]] as her.

Her fan nickname is [i]Zekamashi[/i], Shimakaze spelled backwards due to pre-1946 Japanese orthography reading horizontal writing right-to-left, after it was written on an [[innertube]] on a Rensouhou-chan.

Character design by [[Shizuma Yoshinori]], voiced by [[Sakura Ayane]].

title: project_luminasys
body:
Project Luminasys (Luminescence, alternatively spelled Luminasis) is an ongoing idol project made by the artist [[ohisashiburi]] comprised of 14 characters, and 5 teams. The setting for the world isn't known as a whole and only given very sparely. The following information may not be 100 percent accurate.

h4. Characters

h5. PURE♡LOVE
= Is the main unit of the project in where our main character is apart of.
* [[Kirara Akaru]] (Cv. Yui Horie): An ordinary middle school student with a troubled past. A happy go lucky attitude, it seems that she tries her best to stay positive despite her situation. She is the main character of the series. Kirara started her idol activities at [[komurasaki kuo|Kuo's]] recommendation. After her mother is rendered comatose from an accident, she is left to live with a distant relative.

* [[Komurasaki Kuo]] (Cv. Maaya Uchida): Kuo is the twin sister of mignon unit member [[komurasaki muma|Muma]]. She has a strong sense of inferiority towards her older sister, and deems her a rival; though one sided. After her sister had made her debut as an idol, she had decided to make a career for herself as an idol, aswell.

* [[Yurizono Eryu]] (Cv. Hikasa Yoko): As the sole daughter of an affluent family, she is subsequently forced to listen to her parents nagging for her to take over the family business, and thus give up on her dreams. It seems she refused. She is acquainted with [[hatane rona|Rona]] in school, but due to her disappearing, she had became a loner.

h5. MIGNON

* [[Komurasaki Muma]] (Cv. Hidaka Rina): The older twin sister of [[komurasaki kuo|Kuo]]. She is said to have a very mature personality for her age. 'muma' is her stage name.

* [[Kano Shirayuki]] (Cv. Kayano Ai): The leader of the mignon unit group, and the daughter of a famous company within the universe. Her appearance is deceiving, as she likes to cause mischief regularly and play pranks on others. Its mentioned that she has a younger brother who looks exactly like her.

* [[Fukami Levy]] (Cv. Wakai Yuki): She proclaims herself to be 'cool' and 'mysterious'. Has an "accent when she speaks":[/posts/3937411?q=fukami_levy], and appears to swear a lot. It's said that she has an extreme secondary illness, though undisclosed. 

h5. CAROL / CALOR

* [[Katanaya Mashiko]] (Cv. Minami Tanaka): She is the youngest out of all the Luminasys characters. Characterized by a boyish appearance, she acts very mature for her age.

* [[Sazanami Tsudzuru]] (Cv. Hibiku Yamamura): She is often seen wearing very traditional Japanese clothing, and most of her outfits will by only slightly modernized. Tzudzuru is said to be a delinquent that often skips class.

h5. MYSTIC NOVA / MYSTICNOVA
= It is a team made up of foreign students only. Unlike pure♡love, which emphasizes cuteness, it emphasizes charisma.
* [[Svetlana (project luminasys)|]] (alternatively Svetlana): She is a Russian student studying at the school. She has very bad anxiety and is typically unable to speak up, whether it be for herself, or for others. Only a select few are able to get her to speak. Since her real name seems to be Hikaru Hoshimachi, the initial setting of her being an international student is not made clear. Whether she is an international student or of mixed race, is up in airs.

* [[Layla (ohisashiburi)|]] (alternatively Lyla): A Brazilian student, perhaps due to that, she is the only character with darker skin out of all of the group(s). She is the tallest out of all the characters in the series, and is said to be very good at lying and deception.

* [[Yuson (ohisashiburi)|]] (alternatively Meteor): A Korean student. Due to her overwhelming talent in singing, dancing and makeup, she is very popular with other teenage girls and has many followers on social media.

h5. RESARCANA
= Although a unit, there is only one member.
* [[Hatane Rona]]: Rona is a girl said to be blessed and adored by god, beautiful looks and incredible talent, she is envied. Early on, she used to be acquainted with [[yurizono eryu|Eryu]] growing up. However, it is undisclosed the reason as to why she no longer met with her. Due to another series of mistakes made by her, she had became the reason as to why [[kirara akaru|Kirara's]] mother became comatose, and subsequently making her an orphan. 

h5. MISC
= These characters did not exist initially, but were added later on.
* [[kusuri nemui|Kusuri Nemui]]: A girl with very long hair in drills, she is shown to be a very big fan of [[kirara akaru|Kirara]].

* [[okuoka kimi|Okuoka Kimi]]: A girl with tomboyish characteristics. Her distinctive features are her very sharp eyes and multiple piercings. She is a singer/songwriter, and is shown to be in a unit with Nemui (though unnamed as of now).

h4. External links

* "Youtube":[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UClPh7Axlf5SbRK_CsSzQlBA]
* "Twitter":[https://twitter.com/pjt_Lmnsys]

title: enterprise_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the [i][[USS Enterprise (CV-6)]][/i] in [[Azur Lane]]. Character designed by [[Hao (patinnko)]], voiced by [[Ishikawa Yui]].

Not to be confused with [[Enterprise (hms) (azur lane)|HMS Enterprise]].

She has [[very long hair|very long]], [[grey hair|grey]], [[aqua hair|aqua]], or [[white hair]], [[grey eyes|silver]] to dull [[blue eyes]], and is [[large breasts|well-endowed]]. She wears a white [[peaked cap]], a [[sleeveless]], [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]] and [[necktie]], a [[black skirt|black]], [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]] with [[gold trim]], [[black thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[knee boots]]. She has an open long [[black coat]] with red inner lining that reaches her feet and hangs loosely on her shoulders. Her [[rigging]] is composed of a [[flight deck]] with yellow markings, including the letters "EN," and bow with island superstructure.

She is frequently depicted with her companion bald eagle, though officially unnamed, has been nicknamed "[[Grim (azur lane)|]]."

title: noshiro_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Japanese light cruiser [i]Noshiro[/i], introduced in the [i]Swirling Cherry Blossoms[/i] event of December 2019.

She has [[long hair|long]] black hair and [[skin-covered horns]] that [[gradient horns|gradate]] to [[red horns|red]]  and wearing a [[black serafuku]], [[white sailor collar]], and [[pantyhose]]. She is also seen with a [[katana]] slung to her back. A second katana and a [[wakizashi]] are shown on her left/portside rig with a quadruple 61 cm torpedo mount. On her right/starboard rig are her two 15.2 cm twin main gun mounts and a second quad torpedo mount. She also carries 25 mm twin AA mounts on [[thigh strap|thigh straps]].

In real life, she was brought into service as the new flagship of the Second Torpedo Squadron to replace [[Jintsuu (Azur Lane)|]], sunk in Kolombangara. She served in this role until she was sunk in the battle of Leyte Gulf.

Voiced by [[Inami Anju]].

title: helena_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the USS [i]Helena[/i] (CL-50). Character design by [[Realmbw]], voiced by Chuujou Tomoyo.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair]] with a [[purple hair|purple]] inner shade and [[ahoge]], and [[purple eyes]]. As she was the only of the [i]Brooklyn[/i]-class that failed to survive the war, she has a shorter height than her sisters. 

Her outfit is the same as her sisters: a [[two-tone dress]] of white and Navy Blue with [[side slit|side openings]], black [[elbow gloves]], [[black thighhighs]] with [[garter straps]], [[black panties]], and [[rudder footwear]].

Her [[rigging]] consists of her five historic 152 mm triple mounts in two separate hull pieces, one of which is used as a handgun. Her SG [[radar]] is visible as a [[hair ornament]], a reference to how she had historically been the first to detect inbound Japanese forces in the battles of Cape Esperance and Naval Guadalcanal and likewise reflects in her in-game skills. She also has a 28 mm quad [[anti-aircraft gun]] mount directly to her back.

She was torpedoed at the attack on Pearl Harbor in December 1941 and was repaired and modernized before returning to service in early 1942. She was sunk in the Battle of Kula Gulf on 6 July 1943.

title: ishtar_(fate)
body:
The Babylonian goddess of love and war, she is an Archer-class pseudo-Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]] using [[Tohsaka Rin]]'s body as a container. Her [[weapon]] is [[Heavenly Boat Maanna]]. In [[Fate/Strange Fake]], [spoiler]she possesses the body of an Einzbern homunculus named [[Fillia (fate)|]].[/spoiler] 

Ishtar is considered a separate character from [[Tohsaka Rin]] for tagging purposes. Only tag both if both are present in the image.

title: tomoe_gozen_(fate)
body:
Archer-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Referenced in the Babylonia singularity as one of the heroes Gilgamesh summoned to defend his kingdom, and who later perished defeating an enemy commander. She makes her playable debut in [[Shimousa (fate/grand order)|]] as [b]Archer of Inferno[/b]. Despite her steadfast nature and her fiery and graceful style of combat (she wields a [[sword]], a [[naginata]], and a [[bow (weapon)|]] with great proficiency), she has a more playful side (shown in My Room where she expresses great interest in playing video games).

Has [[black horns]], due to having some oni ancestry. These only become visible starting with her second ascension. The horns are initially [[black horns|black]] but turn [[red horns|red horns]] for her third ascension. She also has [[very long hair|very long]] [[aqua hair|aqua]], [[light blue hair|light blue]], or [[grey hair]] (sometimes in a [[ponytail]], or with a white [[headband]] and a [[red bow]]) and [[red eyes]]. Usually wears a [[short kimono|short]] [[white kimono]] with an [[obi]] and [[detached sleeves]], and [[hakama pants]] with [[side slit|side slits]]. Sometimes she also has [[kote]] and [[kusazuri]]. Her later outfit looks like a [[sleeveless turtleneck]] showing some [[sideboob]]. Her kote and kusazuri looks more colorful.

[b]Character Design[/b]: [[Shirabi]]
[b]Voice Actress[/b]: [[Kanemoto Hisako]]

title: medb_(fate)
body:
Rider-class Servant from [[Fate/Grand Order]] first appearing in the [[E Pluribus Unum (fate/grand order)|]] singularity.

The Queen of Connacht in Irish mythology. Uses a riding crop in battle, and summons her wagon [spoiler]that she uses to kidnap men to sleep with her[/spoiler] as her Noble Phantasm. Infamous for her extreme hypersexuality, to the point where her skill in riding (a man) was one of the criteria for her Rider designation.

title: taneshima_popura
body:
A character in the [[Working!!]] anime series. She is a 17-year old girl who is [[oppai loli|very short but busty despite her age]], yet she claims that she wants to be taller.

She has [[brown eyes]], [[very long hair|very long]] [[brown hair]] worn in a [[high ponytail]] with [[choppy bangs]] and usually wears the [[wagnaria uniform]].

She doesn't like being called short and will sometimes deny being short. When someone calls her short she often uses her catchphrase ''ちっちゃくないよ!'' (Chicchaku Nai Yo) roughly translating to "I'm not tiny!".

Her official height has never been revealed but is believed to be close to 140cm. 

She is voiced by [[Asumi Kana]].

title: kagarino_kirie
body:
The main female protagonist in [i][[bishoujo mangekyou: norowareshi densetsu no shoujo|Norowareshi Densetsu no Shoujo]][/i], the first title in the [[Bishoujo Mangekyou (series)|]] series.

At first glance, [b]Kirie[/b] is a beautiful student at an all-girls school that [[onogami shigehiko|Onogami]] teaches at, but secretly she is a 300+ year old [[vampire]] with an air of superiority. Being adamant in her opinion that humans are an inferior species. She keeps a calm and composed persona while also not speaking much in public.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] styled in [[twintails]] with [[wispy bangs]] and [[sidelocks]], [[red eyes]] ([[blue eyes]] in public), and [[small breasts]].

title: maegami-chan_(tawawa)
body:
A character from [i][[Getsuyoubi no Tawawa]][/i].

A girl who began going out and cohabiting with one of her high school teachers right after she graduated. [spoiler]They eventually [[husband and wife|got married]] in post #3155816, and had [[maegami-chan's_daughter_(tawawa)|their first child]] in post #3375994.[/spoiler]

She used to live next to Ai-chan's "onii-chan"'s single apartment with the teacher. As of post #3206839, she has become neighbors with [[Ai-chan_(Tawawa)|]]. In the manga, she has a mother with even larger breasts that looks young enough to be mistaken as her sister, and lives in the same apartment as [[Cheer-chan (Tawawa)|]]'s childhood friend.

Her name comes from the [[wispy bangs|choppy]] [[long bangs]] that partially [[hair over eyes|conceal her eyes]].

In isekai depictions, she always has [[bright pupils]].

title: star_(signalis)
body:
Replika Type STAR (Sicherheitstechniker-Aufseher-Replika | Security Technician Guard Replika ) Star.

The Star is a character / unit in the game [[Signalis]].

Star units act as security forces and guards, usually led by an officer Star unit. 

Ingame, Star units are much more durable and powerful compared to other enemies. Some Star units will come equipped with a [[riot shield]], which provides complete protection from the players weapons except for certain armour piercing weaponry or attacks while the shield is down.

Gameplay Spoilers :
[spoilers] Two Star units can be found ingame. An injured uncorrupted Star unit will be found within the upper level of the facility, who tells Elster the Gestalt she's looking for is likely within the mines but warns her not to enter the facility. Another injured Star is found within the mines, accompanied by a crying [[Eule_(signalis) | Eule Unit]] 

h6. Appearance
On top of being an [[android]], the Star unit has: [[short hair | short]] [[black hair]], a [[bob cut]], [[wispy bangs]], [[blue eyes]], and are sometimes seen wearing a [[mouth mask]].
They usually wield a [[revolver]], [[stun baton]], and oftentimes a [[riot shield]].

title: sig_sauer_p320
body:
The [b]SIG P320[/b] is a modular striker-fired semi-automatic [b][[handgun]][/b] made by [[SIG Sauer]]. It features a separated trigger group which can be switched between various models, utilizing a striker-fired mechanism in lieu of a double action only hammer system. Available in various calibers.

On 19 January 2017, the P320 was chosen to replace the Beretta M9 as the main service pistol of the US Army.

The P320 has also become infamous for its issues with uncommanded discharges, usually resulting from the gun being dropped or inserting/removing the gun from a holster. Many US organizations have banned or discontinued use of the P320 due to safety concerns; uncommanded discharge incidents have also led to several lawsuits. SIG has maintained that the P320 is a safe pistol, and blame these incidents on user error. The whole ordeal spawned countless jokes about the P320, and SIG themselves. 

h4. External links
* "Official SIG Sauer website: P320":https://www.sigsauer.com/firearms/pistols/p320.html
* "Wikipedia: SIG P320":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SIG_Sauer_P320

title: tennessee_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the battleship USS [i]Tennessee[/i] (BB-43). Voiced by [[Satou Rina]].

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]], [[blue eyes]], [[large breasts]], and [[dark-skinned female|dark skin]]. Her uniform consists of a [[white dress|white]] [[microdress]] styled after a [[double-breasted]] [[naval uniform]]. Her sleeves are [[detached sleeves|detached]] from the dress, covering her shoulders and wrapping around the back [tn](see [[California (Azur Lane)|California]])[/tn]. She has a has a [[blue coat|navy blue]], [[long coat]] tied around her neck with a [[high collar]] and a tiny [[necktie]]. She wears [[black thighhighs]], with "1919" written on her left thighhigh in reference to her launch date, and a [[white headwear|white]] [[peaked cap]] with orange-yellow paddle-like structures coming out the sides. 

Her [[rigging]] is composed of two hull structures to her side, four triple-[[ship turret|turrets]], and smaller AA-mounts on the the hulls. 

h4. Skins
* !post #2958376: Default

h5. History
Moored inboard of [i]West Virginia[/i], she escaped damage for the most part during the attack on Pearl Harbor. She was quickly restored to service in escort duties before being recalled to the West Coast in mid-1942 for an extensive reconstruction a la [[South Dakota (Azur Lane)|]].

Re-entering active service in 1943, she participated in shore bombardment duties from the Aleutians to Leyte, joining her sister in the battle line that engaged "Nishimura's fleet":/pools/9549 in the last battleship-to-battleship engagement in history. Later seeing service in Iwo Jima and Okinawa, the pair were decommissioned in 1947 and scrapped 12 years later.

body: Matt is a character from [[Death Note]], he is Mello's friend who lends him aid on the [[yagami light|Kira]] case. Like Mello and [[Near (Death note)|]], and earlier, [[L (death note)|]], Matt was raised at Wammy's House—[[Watari (death note)|]]'s orphanage for gifted children in Winchester, [[England]].

title: ryuk
body: Ryuk is one of the main characters of [[Death Note]]. He is a [[Shinigami]] and the original owner of the [[Death Note (object)|]] that [[Yagami Light]] gets his hands on, having dropped it into the human world to begin with just to see what will happen. He is primarily motivated by boredom and amusement.

title: death_note
body:
A supernatural/gothic thriller manga series written by Ooba Tsugumi and illustrated by [[Obata Takeshi]] and published on [[Weekly Shounen Jump]] on 2003. An anime adaption produced by [[Madhouse]] was aired from 2006 to 2007. There are also live-action adaptions, novels, and sequels.

[[Yagami Light]] is a brilliant young man who one day finds a black notebook called a [[Death Note (object)|]] which can kill anyone whose name is written in it. Light uses it to secretly kill criminals, drawing the attention of Interpol and the enigmatic detective [[L (death note)|]]. This ultimately leads him to a psychological game of cat-and-mouse as Light avoids the authorities while attempting to create a new world in his own vision.

title: yagami_light
body:
Main character of the [[Death Note]] anime and manga series. Light is a highly intelligent high school student who gets his hands on a [[Death Note (object)|]] dropped into the human world by a [[shinigami]], and decides to use it to change the world, becoming the vigilante killer known as "Kira" and coming into conflict with both the law enforcement of the world and the mysterious detective known only as [[L (Death Note)|]].

He is quite known for his '[[Just as Planned (meme)|]]' look and 'The [[God of the New World (meme)|]]' expression which gained [[meme]] status.

h4.External links
* "Wikipedia: Light Yagami":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_Yagami

title: amane_misa
body: Amane Misa is a fictional character in the manga series [[Death Note]], created by Tsugumi Ohba and Takeshi Obata. A famous model, Misa seeks out Kira ([[Yagami Light]]) as she supports his cause to "cleanse the world of evil". Using her own Death Note, a notebook that allows its owner to kill anyone simply by knowing their name and face that she received from the Shinigami [[Rem (death_note)|]], Misa does everything she can to aid Light.

body: AI prompter

title: laki_(one_piece)
body:
Laki is a Shandian warrior in Skypiea

She is a [[tall_female|tall]] [[black_hair|black-haired]] woman, with  [[parted_bangs|parted bangs]] and a long [[ponytail]]. Her eyes are depicted as both [[green_eyes|dark green]] or [[black_eyes|black]].
Like all the sky people she has two [[wings|small wings]] on her back. Her outfit is a light [[cleavage|revealing tunic]] with an [[midriff|exposed midriff]] and [[red_pants|light-red pants]] that looks like clothes worn by [[native_american_clothes|native americans]]. She is often [[barefoot]], like other Shandians.

title: cyberpunk_(series)
body:
A [[science fiction]] franchise originally created by Mike Pondsmith. The "original" [[cyberpunk]] media franchise that, while not the first, is so influential that the entire genre is named after it.

h4. Installments
* Cyberpunk (TTRPG, 1988) - also known as [i]Cyberpunk 2020[/i] and [i]Cyberpunk Red[/i] in later editions.
* [[Cyberpunk 2077]] (video game, 2020)
* [[Cyberpunk: Edgerunners]] (anime, 2022)

title: pilar_(cyberpunk)

body:

title: petite
body:
A relatively small female body type that still retains developed body features such as slightly curvy hips or a [[pear-shaped figure]].

Tall women are not petite even if they are slender. Such images should be tagged [[skinny]].

Petite should only be used for people of natural size. An exceptionally small person should instead be tagged [[minigirl]].

Petite women with exceptionally [[curvy]] bodies and [[wide hips]] should be tagged as [[shortstack]]s.

For female characters that appear fully prepubescent, use [[child]] if the image is rated general or sensitive, depending on the situation as long they are not sexually depicted, otherwise use [[loli]] if the image is rated questionable or explicit. See [[howto:rate]] for more.

title: cyborg
body:
An organism that is made up of both [b]cyb[/b]ernetic and [b]org[/b]anic components. In anime, this generally refers to humans that have been altered to be partially [[robot]]ic.

It can be difficult to tell a cyborg apart from an [[android]], especially when dealing with [[original]] characters and those whose origins are unknown. In cases like these, one should examine any visible robotic components. If they appear to be added-on or function as [[prosthesis|prosthetics]], that character is likely a cyborg. If you are unable to determine whether the character is a cyborg or purely robotic, it's best to tag them as [[android]] until more information can be found.

title: cyberpunk
body:
A [[science fiction]] genre. Basic themes include the dehumanizing effects of technology, and the accompanying societal breakdown. Think dark and dirty, with lots of [[wire]]s and [[neon lights|neon]].

[b]Cyberpunk[/b] is a postmodern dystopian genre noted for its focus on [b]”high tech and low life"[/b]. The name is a portmanteau of cybernetics and punk, and was originally coined by American science fiction author Bruce Bethke as the title of his short Sci-Fi story [i]Cyberpunk[/i], written in 1980.

Cyberpunk can cover numerous themes and motifs but generally involve reflecting on the current anxieties of society and amping them up to an extreme; things like mass surveillance, corporate monopolization, climate change, mass media, artificial intelligence and any other themes can thus be accomodated by a cyberpunk setting.

For the series of the same name, see [[Cyberpunk (series)]].

title: clair_obscur:_expedition_33
body:
A dark fantasy turn-based RPG developed by Sandfall Interactive and released in 2025.

Set in a Belle Époque-inspired world where each year, everyone of a certain age is erased from existence by a mysterious being called the Paintress. The player controls members of "Expedition 33," a group trying to stop her before the next erasure.

h4. Characters

h5. Main party
* [[Gustave (clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 
* [[Lune (clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 
* [[Maelle (Clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 
* [[Sciel (Clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 
* [[Verso (Clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 
* [[Monoco (Clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 

h5. Other major characters
* [[Esquie (Clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 

h5. NPCs
* [[Francois (Clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]] 
* [[Sophie (Clair Obscur: Expedition 33)|]]
